Standard
ADaM-IG 1.1
Study Name
COVE
Study Description
A Phase 3, Randomized, Stratified, Observer-Blind, Placebo-Controlled Study to Evaluate the Efficacy, Safety, and Immunogenicity of mRNA-1273 SARS-CoV-2 Vaccine in Adults Aged 18 Years and Older
Protocol Name
mRNA-1273-P301
Metadata Name
Study COVE Data Definitions

Analysis Results Metadata - Summary

Table 14.2.2.1.3.1.1Analysis of Vaccine Efficacy of mRNA-1273 to Prevent COVID-19* Based on Adjudication Committee Assessments Starting 14 Days After Second Injection

The primary efficacy objective will be evaluated by the VE of mRNA-1273 to prevent the first occurrence of COVID-19 starting 14 days after the second injection of IP.

Table 14.2.4.1.1.1.3.1Summary of Binding Antibody Specific to SARS-CoV-2 Spike Protein by MSD by Baseline SARS-CoV-2 Status

The secondary immunogenicity objective will be evaluated by the following endpoints: (a) Geometric mean titer (GMT) of S protein-specific bAb on Day 1, Day 29, Day 57 (b) GMFR of S protein-specific bAb relative to Day 1 on Day 29, Day 57

ADVS Vital Signs Analysis Dataset BASIC DATA STRUCTURE One record per subject per parameter per assessment Analysis USUBJID, PARAMCD, AVISITN, ADT, VISITNUM, VSTPT advs.xpt
ADAE Adverse Event Analysis Dataset OCCURRENCE DATA STRUCTURE One record per subject per adverse event Analysis USUBJID, AEBODSYS, AEDECOD, AESTDTC, AEENDTC, AESEQ adae.xpt
ADCM Concomitant Medication Analysis Dataset OCCURRENCE DATA STRUCTURE One record per subject per medication Analysis USUBJID, CMTRT, CMSTDTC, CMENDTC adcm.xpt
ADDV Deviation Analysis Dataset OCCURRENCE DATA STRUCTURE One record per subject per deviation Analysis USUBJID, DVCAT, DVSCAT, DVSTDTC, DVTERM addv.xpt
ADEX Treatment Exposure Analysis Dataset OCCURRENCE DATA STRUCTURE One record per subject per administration Analysis USUBJID, EXSTDTC adex.xpt
ADMH Medical History Analysis Dataset OCCURRENCE DATA STRUCTURE One record per subject per medical history Analysis USUBJID, MHCAT, MHTERM, MHDECOD, MHSTDTC admh.xpt

Derived
Set to DS.DSTERM where DSCAT='DISPOSITION EVENT' and DSSCAT='END OF STUDY' AND DSDECOD not in ('COMPLETED', 'ADVERSE EVENT', 'SAE', 'PHYSICIAN DESICION', 'WITHDRAWAL BY SUBJECT', 'PROTOCOL DEVIATION', 'OTHER', 'DEATH') Set to 'Adverse Event' if DS.DSDECOD is 'ADVERSE EVENT' Set to 'Serious Adverse Event' if DS.DSDECOD is 'SAE' Set to 'Protocol Deviation' if DS.DSDECOD is 'PROTOCOL DEVIATION' Set to 'Other' if DS.DSDECOD is 'OTHER' Set to 'Physician Decision' if DS.DSDECOD is 'PHYSICIAN DESICION' Set to 'Withdrawal of Consent by Participant' if DS.DSDECOD is 'WITHDRAWAL BY SUBJECT' Set to 'Death' if DS.DSDECOD='DEATH'

Create one PARAM per subject per PARCAT1 per ATPTREF by following Solicited AR Summary Analysis Dataset Parameter Code
AVALVLM Analysis Value integer 8
PARAMCD IN (
"ARTHRDUR" (Number of Days for Arthralgia),
"CHILLDUR" (Number of Days for Chills),
"ERYTHDUR FATIGDUR",
"FEVERDUR" (Number of Days for Fever),
"HEADADUR" (Number of Days for Headache),
"LYMPHDUR" (Number of Days for Lymphadenopathy),
"MYALGDUR" (Number of Days for Myalgia),
"NAUSEDUR" (Number of Days for Nausea),
"PAINDUR" (Number of Days for Pain),
"SWELLDUR" (Number of Days for Swelling)
) 		Number of Days of Solicited AR Per Subject, Per Symptom and Per Vaccination integer 8
Derived
1. Get number of days from ADAR: Count total number of records with ATOXGRN>0 per subject, per symptom (ADAR.PARAMCD) and per vaccination (ATPTREF). If there are more than one record within same day (ADAR.ATPTGR1), then count it once only 2. Get number of days from ADARP7D: Count total number of records with ATOXGRN>0 and ADAR.P7D.ATPTGR1N>=8 per subject, per symptom (ADARP7D.PARAMCD) and per vaccination (ATPTREF). If there are more than one record within same day (ADARP7D.ATPTGR1), then count it once only 3. Calculate the sum of the number of records from steps 1 and 2 per subject per, per symptom (PARAMCD) and per vaccination (ATPTREF)
PARAMCD IN (
"LOCDUR" (Number of Days for Local Solicited AR),
"SYSDUR" (Number of Days for Systemic Solicited AR)
) 		Number of Days of Solicited AR Per Symptom Category (Local or Systemic), Per Vaccination integer 8
Derived
1. Get number of days from ADAR: Count total number of records with ATOXGRN>0 per subject, per symptom category (ADAR.PARCAT1) and per vaccination (ATPTREF). If there are more than one record within same day (ADAR.ATPTGR1), then count it once only 2. Get number of days from ADARP7D: Count total number of records with ATOXGRN>0 and ADARP7D.ATPTGR1N>=8 per subject, per symptom category (ADARP7D.PARCAT1) and per vaccination (ATPTREF). If there are more than one record within same day (ADARP7D.ATPTGR1), then count it once only 3. Calculate the sum of the number of records from steps 1 and 2 per subject per, per symptom (PACAT1) and per vaccination (ATPTREF)
PARAMCD = "ANYDUR" (Number of Days for Any Solicited AR) Number of Days of Solicited AR Per Subject and Per Vaccination integer 8
Derived
1. Get number of days from ADAR: Count total number of records with ATOXGRN>0 per subject and per vaccination (ATPTREF). If there are more than one record within same day (ADAR.ATPTGR1), then count it once only 2. Get number of days from ADARP7D: Count total number of records with ATOXGRN>0 and ADARP7D.ATPTGR1N>=8 per subject and per vaccination (ATPTREF). If there are more than one record within same day (ADARP7D.ATPTGR1), then count it once only 3. Calculate the sum of the number of records from steps 1 and 2 per subject per and per vaccination (ATPTREF)
AVALC Analysis Value (C) text 100
Derived
Derived worse case of each AR symptom occurred within 7 days per vaccination (ATPTREF) where PARAMCD in (WLYMPH, WPAIN, WERYTH, WSWELL, WHEAD, WFATIGUE, WMYALGIA, WARTHR, WNAUSEA, WCHILLS, WFEVER): Set to ADAR.AVALC where ADAR.ATOXGR is the worse case per AR symptom within 7 Days per vaccination (ATPTREF) Note: The higher number of ADAR.ATOXGRN, the worse symptom grade

Derived
Create a record for PARAM = 'COVID-19' for each positive RT-PCR if following conditions are met: 1. RT-PCR is positive (MB.MBTESTCD='SARSCOV2' and MB.MBSTRESC is in ('DETECTED' or ‘POSITIVE’) after first dose (MB.MBDTC > ADSL.TR01SDT (non-missing)) and VISIT is not in ('Visit 2 Day 29', 'Participant Decision Visit / OL-D1') ) 2. if symptom(s) occurred within +/-14 days window of positive PCR date (symptom event found from ADSYMP where ADSYMP.AVALC=Y and MB.MBDTC-14 <= ADSYMP.ADT <= MB.MBDTC+14): (a) at least two systemic symptom events found from ADSYMP where PARAMCD in ('FEVER', 'CHILLS', 'MYALGIA'/'BODYACHE', 'HEADACHE', 'STHROAT', 'NLSMELL'/'NLTASTE') where 'NLSMELL' and/or 'NLTASTE' are considered as one symptom, 'MYALGIA' and/or 'BODYACHE' are considered as one symptom, or (b) at least one respiratory symptom event found from ADSYMP where PARAMCD in ('COUGH', 'SHBREATH', 'DIBREATH', 'CEPNEU', 'REPNEU'). For 'CEPNEU' and 'REPNEU', use ADSYMP.ASTDT in place of ADSYMP.ADT and use ADSYMP.ADT when ADSYMP.ASTDT is missing
PARAMCD = "COVIDS" (COVID-19 (Considering Scheduled RT-PCR)) COVID-19 (Considering Scheduled RT-PCR) text 100
Derived
Create a record for PARAM = 'COVID-19 (Considering Scheduled RT-PCR)' if following conditions are met: 1. RT-PCR is positive (MB.MBTESTCD='SARSCOV2', MB.MBSTRESC is in ('DETECTED', ‘POSITIVE) after first dose (MB.MBDTC > ADSL.TR01SDT (non-missing))) 2. if symptom(s) occurred within +/-14 days window of positive PCR date (symptom event found from ADSYMP where ADSYMP.AVALC=Y and MB.MBDTC-14 <= ADSYMP.ADT <= MB.MBDTC+14): (a) at least two systemic symptom events found from ADSYMP where PARAMCD in ('FEVER', 'CHILLS', 'MYALGIA'/'BODYACHE', 'HEADACHE', 'STHROAT', 'NLSMELL'/'NLTASTE') where 'NLSMELL' and/or 'NLTASTE' are considered as one symptom, 'MYALGIA' and/or 'BODYACHE' are considered as one symptom, or (b) at least one respiratory symptom event found from ADSYMP where PARAMCD in ('COUGH', 'SHBREATH', 'DIBREATH', 'CEPNEU', 'REPNEU'). For 'CEPNEU' and 'REPNEU', use ADSYMP.ASTDT in place of ADSYMP.ADT and use ADSYMP.ADT when ADSYMP.ASTDT is missing

PARAMCD = "COVIDSD" (COVID-19 (Secondary Definition)) COVID-19 (Secondary Definition) text 100
Derived
Create record for PARAM = 'COVID-19' for each RT-PCR is Positive (Secondary Definition)' if following conditions are met: 1. Select all subjects where RT-PCR is Positive (MB.MBSTRESC=DETECTED or POSITIVE due to prompt symptom) after First Dose (MBDTC>ADSL.TR01SDTC) and VISIT is not 'VISIT 2 Day 29' or 'Participant Decision Visit / OL-D1' 2. If a systemic symptom occurred within +/-14 days window of date with detected /positive as test result (a) any systemic symptom event found from ADSYMP where PARAMCD in ('FEVER', 'CHILLS', 'COUGH', 'SHBREATH', 'DIBREATH', 'FATIGUE', 'MYALGIA', 'BODYACHE', 'HEADACHE', 'NLTASTE', 'NLSMELL', 'STHROAT', 'NASALCON', 'RUNNOSE', 'NAUSEA', 'VOMIT', 'DIARRHEA')
PARAMCD = "COVIDSDS" (COVID-19 (Secondary Definition and Considering Scheduled RT-PCR)) COVID-19 (Secondary Definition and Considering Scheduled RT-PCR) text 100
Derived
Create a record for PARAM = 'COVID-19 (Secondary Definition and Considering Scheduled RT-PCR)' for each positive RT-PCR test after first dose if at least one systemic symptom occurred within +/-14 days window of positive PCR date: ADSYMP.PARAMCD in ('FEVER', 'CHILLS', 'COUGH', 'SHBREATH', 'DIBREATH', 'FATIGUE', 'MYALGIA', 'BODYACHE', 'HEADACHE', 'NLTASTE', 'NLSMELL', 'STHROAT', 'NASALCON', 'RUNNOSE', 'NAUSEA', 'VOMIT', 'DIARRHEA') and ADSYMP.AVALC=Y and MB.MBDTC-14 <= ADSYMP.ADT <= MB.MBDTC+14
PARAMCD = "COVIDSEV" (Severe COVID-19) Severe COVID-19 text 100
Derived
Create record for PARAM='Severe COVID-19' if following conditions are met: 1. Subject with PARAMCD='COVID', 2. At least one severe symptom (a) or (b) occurred within -14/+28 days window of positive PCR date (a) ADSYMP.PARAMCD in ('RR30', 'HR125', 'OXYGEN93', 'O2SAT93', 'PAO2F300', 'RF', 'ARDS', 'S90D60', 'VASOPRES', 'ARDYSF', 'HEPDYSF', 'NEURDYSF', 'ICU') and ADSYMP.AVALC='Y' and ((PCRDT-14 <= (ADT, ASTDT, or AENDT) <= PCRDT+28) or (ASTDT < PCRDT-14 and AENDT > PCRDT+28)), (b) AE.AESDTH = 'Y' and SUPPAE.QNAM = 'AECVDIAG' and QVAL = 'Y' and PCRDT-14 <= ADSL.DTHDT <= PCRDT+28
PARAMCD = "COVIDSVA" (Severe COVID-19 per Adjudication) Severe COVID-19 per Adjudication text 100
Derived
Create a record for PARAM = 'Severe COVID-19 per Adjudication' if subject has SUPPCE.QVAL containing 'EVENT MEETS THE CHARTER DEFINITION OF SEVERE COVID-19' where QNAM='CEREASOC'
PARAMCD = "COVIDSVS" (Severe COVID-19 (Considering Scheduled RT-PCR)) Severe COVID-19 (Considering Scheduled RT-PCR) text 100
Derived
Create record for PARAM='Severe COVID-19 (Considering Scheduled RT-PCR)' if following conditions are met: 1. Subject with PARAMCD='COVIDS' and AVALC = 'Y' 2. At least one severe symptom occurred within -14/+28 days window of positive PCR date (a) ADSYMP.PARAMCD in ('RR30', 'HR125', 'OXYGEN93', 'PAO2F300', 'RF', 'ARDS', 'S90D60', 'VASOPRES', 'ARDYSF', 'HEPDYSF', 'NEURDYSF', 'ICU') and ADSYMP.AVALC='Y' and (PCRDT-14 <= ADSYMP.ASTDT<= PCRDT+28, or PCRDT-14 <= ADSYMP.AENDT<= PCRDT+28, or (ADSYMP.ASTDT < PCRDT-14 and ADSYMP.AENDT > PCRDT+28), use PCRDT-14 <= ADSYMP.ADT<= PCRDT+28 when ADSYMP.ASTDT and ADSYMP.AENDT are missing) (b) ADSYMP.PARAMCD = 'O2SAT93' and ADSYMP.AVALC='Y' and PCRDT-14 <= ADSYMP.ADT<= PCRDT+28 (c) AE.AESDTH = 'Y' and SUPPAE.QNAM = 'AECVDIAG' and QVAL = 'Y' and PCRDT-14 <= ADSL.DTHDT <= PCRDT+28
PARAMCD = "INFECT" (SARS-CoV-2 Infection Regardless of Symptomatology or Severity) Asymptomatic SARS-CoV-2 Infection text 100
Derived
Create a record for PARAM = 'Asymptomatic SARS-CoV-2 Infection' and AVALC = 'Y' if no prior COVID-19 symptoms (no record created with PARAMCD='COVIDS' or 'COVIDSDS' and AVALC = 'Y' and ADT on/before the earlier date of 1 and 2) and at least one of the following criteria is met: 1. has positive RT-PCR test at Day 29 or participant decision visit (ie, MB.MBTESTCD='SARSCOV2', MB.MBSTRESC is in ('DETECTED', 'POSITIVE') and VISIT in ('Visit 2 Day 29', 'Participant Decision Visit / OL-D1') 2. has seroconversion due to infection (ADIS.CRIT5FL = 'Y' and VISIT doesn't contain 'UNSCH' or 'ILLNESS' or 'CONVALESCENCE')
PARAMCD = "ASYMPINA" (Asymptomatic SARS-CoV-2 Infection per Adjudication) Asymptomatic SARS-CoV-2 Infection per Adjudication text 100
Derived
Create a record for PARAM = 'Asymptomatic SARS-CoV-2 Infection per Adjudication' and AVALC = 'Y' if no prior COVID-19 symptoms (no record created with PARAMCD='COVIDA' or 'COVIDSDS' and AVALC = 'Y' and ADT on/before the earlier date of 1 and 2) and at least one of the following criteria is met: 1. has positive RT-PCR test at Day 29 or participant decision visit (MB.MBTESTCD='SARSCOV2' and MB.MBSTRESC is in ('DETECTED', ‘POSITIVE') and VISIT = 'Visit 2 Day 29' or 'Participant Decision Visit / OL-D1') 2. has seroconversion due to infection (ADIS.CRIT5FL = 'Y' and VISIT doesn't contain 'UNSCH' or 'ILLNESS' or 'CONVALESCENCE')
PARAMCD = "ASYMPINF" (Asymptomatic SARS-CoV-2 Infection) SARS-CoV-2 Infection Regardless of Symptomatology or Severity text 100
Derived
Create a record for PARAM = 'SARS-CoV-2 Infection Regardless of Symptomatology or Severity' if at least one of the following criteria is met: 1. has seroconversion due to infection (ADIS.CRIT5FL = 'Y') 2. has positive RT-PCR test after first dose (MB.MBTESTCD='SARSCOV2', MB.MBSTRESC is in ('DETECTED', 'POSITIVE’) and MB.MBDTC > ADSL.TR01SDT (non-missing)
PARAMCD = "DEATHCVD" (Death Caused by COVID-19) Death Caused by COVID-19 text 100
Derived
Create a record for PARAM = 'Death Caused by COVID-19' if subject has AE.AESDTH = 'Y' and SUPPAE.QNAM = 'AECVDIAG' and QVAL = 'Y' and ADSL.DTHDT is non-missing
AVALC Analysis Value (C) text 50
Derived
Set to 'Y'
PCRDT Date of Positive RT-PCR integer DATE9
Derived
See derivation of PARAM. For PARAMCD = "COVID", "COVIDSD", "COVIDS", "COVIDSDS", set to the date of positive PCR test that meets derivation of corresponding PARAM; For PARAMCD = "COVIDSEV", set to the date of positive PCR test where PARAMCD = "COVID"; For PARAMCD = "COVIDSVS", set to the date of positive PCR test where PARAMCD = "COVIDS"; For PARAMCD = "INFECT", "ASYMPINF", or "ASYMPINA", set to null if PARAM is created based on seroconversion only (not based on positive RT-PCR), else set to the date of PCR test that meets derivation of corresponding PARAM; For PARAMCD = "DEATHCVD", set to the date of most recent post-baseline positive PCR if available (MB.MBDTC where MB.MBTESTCD="SARSCOV2", MB.MBSTRESC is "DETECTED" or "POSITIVE" in upper case, and MBDTC > ADSL.TR01SDT (non-missing)). Otherwise, null.
PCRD29FL Flag for Case Using Positive D29 RT-PCR text 1
Derived
Set to 'Y' if the case is derived using positive RT-PCR at Day 29 ( MB.MBTESTCD = 'SARSCOV2', MB.MBSTRESC is in ('DETECTED' or 'POSITIVE' ), MB.VISIT = 'Visit 2 Day 29', and MB.MBDTC=PCRDT (non-missing)
EVIDINF Evidence for Infection text 15
Derived
For PARAMCD = 'INFECT', 'ASYMPINF', or 'ASYMPINA' Set to 'Virology' if the case is derived based on positive RT-PCR only, Set to 'Serology' if the case is derived based on seroconversion only, Set to 'Virology and Serology' if the case is derived based on both positive RT-PCR and seroconversion
ANL01FL Analysis Flag 01 text 1 Yes Flag
  • • "Y"
Derived
Set to 'Y' for the record with AVALC = 'Y' and earliest ADT per PARAMCD

  • • "Y"

PARAMCD Parameter Code text 8
Assigned

BOD7D if PARAM = 'Burden of Disease Score in 7 Days', BOI7D if PARAM = 'Burden of Infection Score in 7 Days', BOD28D if PARAM = 'Burden of Disease Score in 28 Days', BOI28D if PARAM = 'Burden of Infection Score in 28 Days'
PARAM Parameter text 40 BOD/BOI Score Analysis Parameter Code
  • • "BOD7D" = "Burden of Disease Score in 7 Days"
  • • "BOD28D" = "Burden of Disease Score in 28 Days"
  • • "BOI7D" = "Burden of Infection Score in 7 Days"
  • • "BOI28D" = "Burden of Infection Score in 28 Days"
Assigned

Assign 'Burden of Disease Score in 7 Days', 'Burden of Infection Score in 7 Days', 'Burden of Disease Score in 28 Days', and 'Burden of Infection Score in 28 Days' to each subject who is in ADSL.
AWRANGEVLM Analysis Window Valid Relative Range text 40
PARAMCD IN (
"BOD28D"
) 		Burden of Disease Score text 40
Derived
Set EVENTMO = ADT - RANDDT+1)/30.4375 and create # of records per USUBJID per PARAMCD based on EVENTMO: Create 4 records if EVENTMO >= 18: AWRANGE = 'Randomization through 6 Months', ' After 6 Months through 12 Months', ' After 12 Months through 18 Months', ' After 18 Months through Completion' Create 3 records if EVENTMO >= 12: AWRANGE = 'Randomization through 6 Months', ' After 6 Months through 12 Months', ' After 12 Months through 18 Months' Create 2 records if EVENTMO >= 6: AWRANGE = 'Randomization through 6 Months', ' After 6 Months through 12 Months' Create 1 records, otherwise: AWRANGE = 'Randomization through 6 Months'
PARAMCD IN (
"BOI28D"
) 		Burden of Infection Score text 40
Derived
Set EVENTMO = ADT - RANDDT+1)/30.4375 and create # of records per USUBJID per PARAMCD based on EVENTMO: Create 5 records If EVENTMO >=13 or ADT is missing: AWRANGE= 'Baseline through Month 1', 'After Month 1 through Month 2', 'After Month 2 through Month 7', 'After Month 7 through Month 13', and 'After Month 13 through Month 25' Create 4 records if EVENTMO >=7: AWRANGE= 'Baseline through Month 1', 'After Month 1 through Month 2', 'After Month 2 through Month 7', and 'After Month 7 through Month 13' Create 3 records if EVENTMO >=2: AWRANGE='Baseline through Month 1', 'After Month 1 through Month 2', and 'After Month 2 through Month 7' Create 2 records if EVENTMO >=1: AWRANGE = 'Baseline through Month 1' and 'After Month 1 through Month 2'. Create 1 record, otherwise: AWRANGE = 'Baseline through Month 1'
AWRANGENVLM Analysis Window Valid Relative Range (N) integer 8
PARAMCD IN (
"BOD28D"
) 		Burden of Disease Score integer 8
Derived
Set to 1 if AWRANGE='Randomization through 6 Months'; Set to 2 if AWRANGE='After 6 Months through 12 Months'; Set to 3 if AWRANGE='After 12 Months through 18 Months'; Set to 4 if AWRANGE='After 18 Months through Completion';
PARAMCD IN (
"BOI28D"
) 		Burden of Infection Score integer 8

If ABLFL='Y', then set to 'Y' For post-baseline assessments where AVISITN is non-missing and result (AVAL) is non-missing, per subject per parameter and per AVISIT: Within an AVISIT, set to ‘Y’ for the assessment at scheduled visit (i.e., VISIT doesn't contain "Unsched"). If there are 2 or more assessments with non-missing AVAL on the latest assessment date, use the smaller AVAL, If there is no scheduled visit, set to 'Y' for the assessment closest to the target study day (record with minimum AWTDIFF) in the visit window. If there are 2 or more assessments equal distance to the target study day (AWTDIFFs are same), set to the latest assessment. If there are 2 or more assessments with non-missing AVAL on the latest assessment date, use the smaller AVAL

PARAMCD Parameter Code text 8 COVID-19 Symptom Analysis Dataset Parameter Code

[36 Terms]

Assigned
PARAM Parameter text 200
Derived
Set to PR.PRTRT if source data are from PR Set to HO.HOTERM if source data are from HO and re-code 'ADMITTED TO ICU' to 'Admission to an intensive care unit due to SARS-CoV-2' For SDTM.FAEF as source data: Set to FAEF.FAOBJ and recode follwing symptom terms - Recode to 'Vasopressors Required' if FAEF.FAOBJ='Evidence of Shock Requires Vasopressors' Recode to 'Muscle Aches (Myalgia)' if FAEF.FAOBJ='Myalgia' Recode to 'Runny Nose (Rhinorrhea)' if FAEF.FAOBJ='Rhinorrhea' For SDTM.VS as source data: Set to 'O2 Saturation <=93%' if VSSCAT='COVID-19' and VSTESTCD='OXYSAT' and VSSTRESN is not missing and VSSTRESN<=93 Set to 'Fever' if VSSCAT='COVID-19' and VSTESTCD='TEMP' and VSSTRESN is not missing and VSSTRESN>=38
AVALC Analysis Value (C) text 100
Derived
Set to PR.PROCCUR if source data are from PR Set to HO.HOOCCUR if source data are from HO For SDTM.FAEF as source data: Set to 'Y' if FAEF.FASCAT='COVID-19' and FAEF.FASTRESC in ('MILD', 'MODERATE', 'SEVERE') Set to 'N' if FAEF.FASCAT='COVID-19' and FAEF.FASTRESC = 'NONE' Set to FAEF.FASTRESC if FAEF.FASCAT='COVID-19 SEVERITY' For SDTM.VS as source data: Set to 'Y' if VSTESTCD='OXYSAT' and non-missing VSSTRESN<=93 Set to 'Y' if VSTESTCD='TEMP' and non-missing VSSTRESN>=38 and VSSTRESU='C'
SEV Severity/Intensity text 20
Derived
For SDTM.FAEF as source data: Set to FAEF.FASTRESC if FAEF.FASCAT = 'COVID-19' and FASTRESC in ('MILD', 'MODERATE', 'SEVERE') Set to null, Otherwise
LNKID Link ID text 40
Derived
Set to PRLNKID if source data are from PR, or Set to --SPID in individual source data
SRCDOM Source Data text 20
Derived
Set to FAEF.DOMAIN if source data are from FAEF Set to VS.DOMAIN if source data are from VS Set to PR.DOMAIN if source data are from PR Set to HO.DOMAIN if source data are from HO
SRCSEQ Source Sequence Number integer 8
Derived

Derived

Create # of records based on ADEFF2.PARAMCD and ADEFF2.AVAL: Set to "Burden of Disease Score" if data is derived from ADEFF2.PARAMCD in (BOD7D, BOD28D) Set to 'Burden of Infection Score' if data is derived from ADEFF2.PARAMCD in (BOI7D, BOI28D)
PARAMCD Parameter Code text 8
Assigned
EVENTSEQVLM Event Sequence Number integer 8
PARAMCD = "BOD" Burden of Disease Score Sequence integer 8
Derived
Derive based on the records with ADEFF2.ANL01FL='Y': If ADEFF2.AVAL=0 or 1 where PARAMCD contains 'BOD', assign one record/row with EVENTSEQ=1, If ADEFF2.AVAL=2 where PARAMCD contains 'BOD', assign one record/row with EVENTSEQ=1 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ=2, If ADEFF2.AVAL=3 where PARAMCD contains 'BOD', assign one record/row with EVENTSEQ=1 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ=2 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ=3
PARAMCD = "BOI" Burden of Infection Score Sequence integer 8
Derived
Derive based on the records with ADEFF2.ANL01FL='Y': If ADEFF2.AVAL=0 or 0.5 where PARAMCD contains 'BOI', assign one record/row with EVENTSEQ=1, If ADEFF2.AVAL=1 where PARAMCD contains 'BOI', assign one record/row with EVENTSEQ=1 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ=2, If ADEFF2.AVAL=2 where PARAMCD contains 'BOI', assign one record/row with EVENTSEQ=1 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ=2 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ=3 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ=4, If ADEFF2.AVAL=3 where PARAMCD contains 'BOI', assign one record/row with EVENTSEQ=1 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ=2 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ=3 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ=4 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ=5 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ=6
CNSRVLM Censor integer 8
PARAMCD = "BOD" Burden of Infection Score Censor integer 8
Derived
If EVENTSEQ=1, then do: 1)Set to 1 If ADEFF2.AVAL=0 where PARAMCD contains 'BOD', 2)Set to 0 If ADEFF2.AVAL>=1 where PARAMCD contains 'BOD', If EVENTSEQ=2 or 3, then set to 0 Note: (1 for censor; 0 for event)
PARAMCD = "BOI" Burden of Infection Score Censor integer 8
Derived
If EVENTSEQ=1, then do: 1)Set to 1 If ADEFF2.AVAL=0 where PARAMCD contains 'BOI', 2)Set to 0 If ADEFF2.AVAL>=0.5 where PARAMCD contains 'BOI', If EVENTSEQ>=2, then set to 0 Note: (1 for censor; 0 for event)
EVNTDESCVLM Event or Censoring Description text 100
PARAMCD = "BOD" Burden of Infection Score Censor Description text 100
Derived
For each USUBJID, Set to 'Without COVID-19' if ADEFF2.AVAL=0 where PARAMCD contains 'BOD', Set to 'COVID-19 without hospitalization' if ADEFF2.AVAL= 1 where PARAMCD contains 'BOD', Set to 'COVID-19 with hospitalization' if ADEFF2.AVAL=2 where PARAMCD contains 'BOD', Set to 'Death' if ADEFF2.AVAL=3 where PARAMCD contains 'BOD'
PARAMCD = "BOI" Burden of Infection Score Censor Description text 100
Derived
For each USUBJID, Set to 'No infection’ if ADEFF2.AVAL=0 where PARAMCD contains 'BOI', Set to 'Asymptomatic infection' if ADEFF2.AVAL=0.5 where PARAMCD contains 'BOI', Set to 'COVID-19 without hospitalization' if ADEFF2.AVAL=1 where PARAMCD contains 'BOI', Set to 'COVID-19 with hospitalization' if ADEFF2.AVAL=2 where PARAMCD contains 'BOI', Set to 'Death' if ADEFF2.AVAL=3 where PARAMCD contains 'BOI'
STARTVALVLM Analysis Start Value integer 8
PARAMCD = "BOD" Burden of Disease Score Analysis Start Value integer 8
Derived
Set to 0 if EVENTSEQ=1, Set to the (ADEFF2.ADT- ADSL.RANDDT) if EVENTSEQ=2, Set to the (ADEFF2.ADT- ADSL.RANDDT)+(1e-10) if EVENTSEQ=3
PARAMCD = "BOI" Burden of Infection Score Analysis Start Value integer 8
Derived
Set to 0 if EVENTSEQ=1, set to the (ADEFF2.ADT-ADSL.TR01SDT) if EVENTSEQ=2, Set to the (ADEFF2.ADT-ADSL.TR01SDT) +(1e-10) if EVENTSEQ=3, Set to the (ADEFF2.ADT-ADSL.TR01SDT) +(2e-10) if EVENTSEQ=4, Set to the (ADEFF2.ADT-ADSL.TR01SDT) +(3e-10) if EVENTSEQ=5, Set to the (ADEFF2.ADT-ADSL.TR01SDT) +(4e-10) if EVENTSEQ=6
AVALVLM Analysis Value float 20
PARAMCD = "BOD" Burden of Disease Score Analysis Value float 20
Derived
If where ADEFF2.PARAMCD contains 'BOD' : If ADEFF2.AVAL=0: Set to the earliest date of (ADSL.DTHDT, ADSL.EOSDT, ADSL.EFFCODT, ADSL.AP01EDT) - ADSL.RANDDT if and EVENTSEQ=1, Else: Set to the ADEFF2.ADT- ADSL.RANDDT where EVENTSEQ=1, Set to the ADEFF2.ADT- ADSL.RANDDT+(1e-10) where EVENTSEQ=2 Set to the ADEFF2.ADT- ADSL.RANDDT +(2e-10) where EVENTSEQ=3
PARAMCD = "BOI" Burden of Infection Score Analysis Value float 20
Derived
Set to the earliest date of (ADSL.DTHDT, ADSL.EOSDT, ADSL.EFFCODT, ADSL.AP01EDT) - TR01SDT if ADEFF2.AVAL=0 and EVENTSEQ=1, Set to the ADEFF2.ADT- TR01SDT if EVENTSEQ=1, Set to the ADEFF2.ADT- TR01SDT +(1e-10) if EVENTSEQ=2, Set to the ADEFF2.ADT- TR01SDT +(2e-10) if EVENTSEQ=3, Set to the ADEFF2.ADT- TR01SDT +(3e-10) if EVENTSEQ=4, Set to the ADEFF2.ADT- TR01SDT +(4e-10) if EVENTSEQ=5, Set to the ADEFF2.ADT- TR01SDT +(5e-10) if EVENTSEQ=6

PARAM Parameter text 50
Assigned

Assign 'Total COVID-19 Symptoms Score' to each subject
PARAMCD Parameter Code text 8
Assigned
EVENTSEQ Event Sequence Number integer 8
Derived
Derive based on the records with ADEFF3.ANL01FL='Y' and PARCAT1N = 1 and PPROTFL = ’Y’. Step 1. Calculate temporary variable SUM = sum of AVAL per subject (SUBJID). Step 2. Calcalate min, max, Q1 and Q3 of SUM. Step 3. Assgin EVENTSEQ as follows: If SUM = 0 or 0 < SUM < Q1, assign one record/row with EVENTSEQ = 1; if Q1 <= SUM < Median, assign one record/row with EVENTSEQ = 1 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ = 2; if Median <= SUM < Q3, assign one record/row with EVENTSEQ = 1 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ = 2 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ = 3; if Q3 <= SUM, assign one record/row with EVENTSEQ = 1 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ = 2 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ = 3 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ = 4;
CNSR Censor integer 8
Derived
If EVENTSEQ = 1, then do: 1) Set to 1 If temporary variable SUM (see derivation of EVENTSEQ) = 0, 2) Set to 0 If temporary variable SUM (see derivation of EVENTSEQ) > 0, if EVENTSEQ = 2 or 3 or 4, then set to 0 Note: (1 for censor; 0 for event)
EVNTDESC Event or Censoring Description text 50
Derived
For each USUBJID, Set to ‘No symptom’ if temporary variable SUM (see derivation of EVENTSEQ) = 0, Set to ‘0 < Total COVID-19 Symptoms Score < Q1’ if 0 < temporary variable SUM (see derivation of EVENTSEQ) < Q1, Set to ‘Q1 <= Total COVID-19 Symptoms Score < Median’ if Q1 <= temporary variable SUM (see derivation of EVENTSEQ) < Median, Set to ‘Median <= Total COVID-19 Symptoms Score < Q3’ if Median <= temporary variable SUM (see derivation of EVENTSEQ) < Q3, Set to ‘Q3 <= Total COVID-19 Symptoms Score’ if Q3 <= temporary variable SUM (see derivation of EVENTSEQ).
STARTVAL Analysis Start Value integer 8
Derived
Derive based on the date of first symtom occure per subject (ADEFF3.ADT where FASYMPFL = 'Y') If EVENTSEQ = 1, set to 0. if EVENTSEQ = 2, set to the (ADT - ADSL.TR01SDT). if EVENTSEQ = 3, set to the (ADT - ADSL.TR01SDT) + (1e-10). if EVENTSEQ = 4, set to the (ADT - ADSL.TR01SDT) + (2e-10).
AVAL Analysis Value float 20
Derived
Derive based on the temporary variable SUM (see derivation of EVENTSEQ) and date of first symtom occure per subject (ADEFF3.ADT where FASYMPFL = 'Y') If SUM = 0 where EVENTSEQ = 1, set to the earliest date of (ADSL.DTHDT, ADSL.EOSDT, ADSL.CUTOFFDT) - TR01SDT. if 0 < SUM <= Q1 where EVENTSEQ = 1, set to the ADT - TR01SDT. if Q1 <= SUM < Median , then do: 1) if EVENTSEQ = 1, set to the ADT - TR01SDT. 2) if EVENTSEQ = 2, set to the ADT - TR01SDT + (1e-10). if Median <= SUM < Q3, then do: 1) if EVENTSEQ = 1, set to the ADT - TR01SDT. 2) if EVENTSEQ = 2, set to the ADT - TR01SDT + (1e-10). 3) if EVENTSEQ = 3, set to the ADT - TR01SDT + (2e-10). if Q3 <= SUM, then do: 1) if EVENTSEQ = 1, set to the ADT - TR01SDT. 2) if EVENTSEQ = 2, set to the ADT - TR01SDT + (1e-10). 3) if EVENTSEQ = 3, set to the ADT - TR01SDT + (2e-10). 4) if EVENTSEQ = 4, set to the ADT - TR01SDT + (3e-10).

ANL01FL Analysis Flag 01 text 1 Yes Flag
  • • "Y"
Derived
If ABLFL='Y', then set to 'Y'; for post-baseline assessments where AVISITN is non-missing and result (AVAL) is non-missing, per subject per parameter and per AVISIT per ATPT, Within an AVISIT and ATPT, set to ‘Y’ for the assessment at scheduled visit (i.e., VISIT doesn't contain "UNSCHED"). If there are 2 or more assessments at same visit, set to the last assessment. If there is no scheduled visit, set to 'Y' for the assessment closest to the target study day (record with minimum AWTDIFF) in the visit window. If there are 2 or more assessments equal distance to the target study day (AWTDIFFs are same), set to the last assessment.
ANL02FL Analysis Flag 02 text 1 Yes Flag
  • • "Y"
Derived
For post baseline records where PARAMCD in ('PULSE', 'SYSBP'), per subject per parameter per AVISIT per ATPT where AVISIT NE 'Baseline': Set to 'Y' for the worst toxicity grade (ATOXGRL) where ATOXDSCL is not missing using the following order: Grade 4> Grade 3>Grade 2>Grade 1>Grade 0. If there are more than one worst toxicity grades, then set to the first record
ANL03FL Analysis Flag 03 text 1 Yes Flag
  • • "Y"
Derived
For post baseline records, per subject per parameter per AVISIT where AVISIT NE 'Baseline' Set to 'Y' for the worst toxicity grade (ATOXGRH) where ATOXDSCH is not missing using the following order: Grade 4> Grade 3>Grade 2>Grade 1>Grade 0.If there are more than one worst toxicity grades, then set to the first record

Set to 'Y' if SMQ14NAM is not missing and SMQ14SC is 'Narrow'
ARTERM Collected Term for Adverse Reaction text 40
Derived
Set to import.symp.CETERM where ADAE.AEDECOD = import.symp.CEDECOD
AESOFL Solicited Adverse Reaction? text 1 Yes Flag
  • • "Y"
Derived
Set to 'Y' if ARTERM is not missing
APLFL Anaphylaxis Flag text 1 Yes Flag
  • • "Y"
Derived
Subject level flag based on import.SMQ where SMQNAME='ANAPHYLACTIC REACTION': Set to 'Y' if one of the conditions below is met: 1) AEDECOD in import.SMQ where SMQ.Scope='Narrow' or SMQ.Category = 'A' 2) One AEDECOD in import.SMQ where SMQ.Category = 'B' and One AEDECOD in import.SMQ where SMQ.Category = 'C'. The two identified events should occur within 24 hours based on AESTDTC 3) One AEDECOD in import.SMQ where SMQ.Category = 'D' and [One AEDECOD in import.SMQ where SMQ.Category = 'B' or One AEDECOD in import.SMQ where SMQ.Category = 'C]. The two identified events should occur within 24 hours based on AESTDTC. Note: Use date part to compare if time part is missing, and no date or time imputation
APLREAS Reason for Anaphylaxis text 200
Derived
Refer to the 3 conditions for APLFL: If condition 1 is met, APLREAS = "A narrow term or a term from Category A", If condition 2 is met, APLREAS = "A term from Category B and a term from Category C ", If condition 3 is met, APLREAS = "A term from Category D and [a term from Category B or a term from Category C] " Note: If multiple reasons, concatenate and seperate by '; '
ANL01FL Analysis Flag 01 text 1 Yes Flag
  • • "Y"
Derived
Set to Y if all the conditions below are met: 1) ARTERM in ('Pain', 'Erythema', 'Swelling', 'Underarm Gland Swelling or Tenderness'), 2) MRDSTDY>=8
ANL02FL Analysis Flag 02 text 1 Yes Flag
  • • "Y"
Derived
Set to 'Y' if ANL01FL='Y' and: MRDSTDY=8 and it exists in SDTM.FACE where FATPTNUM=7 by SUBJID, MDOSREF/FATPTREF, ARTERM/FAOBJ
ANL03FL Analysis Flag 03 text 1 Yes Flag
  • • "Y"
Derived
Set to 'Y' if all the conditions below are met: 1) ANL01FL='Y' 2) It exists in SDTM.FACE by SUBJID, MDOSREF/FATPTREF, ARTERM/FAOBJ. That is, subject's events happen in the same period in SDTM.FACE, link ADAE and SDTM.FACE by SUBJID, match the events and corresponding period by ADAE.MDOSREF=FACE.FATPTREF, and ADAE.ARTERM=FACE.FAOBJ 3) If MRDSTDY = 8, the event identified in FACE in step 2) should have max(FATPTNUM) < 7 4) It does not exist in FAAE by SUBJID - MDOSREF/FATPTREF - ARTERM/FAOBJ. Similar linking rule as in Step 2
ANL04FL Analysis Flag 04 text 1 Yes Flag
  • • "Y"
Derived
Set to 'Y' if all the conditions below are met: 1) ANL01FL='Y' 2) It does not exist in FACE by SUBJID - MDOSREF/FATPTREF - ARTERM/FAOBJ

Additional ADaM Variable Definition

ASTDTF Analysis Start Date Imputation Flag text 1
Derived
Set to 'D' if only the day is imputed, or Set to 'M' if the day and the month are imputed
ASTDY Analysis Start Relative Day integer 8
Derived
Set to ASTDT - TR01SDT + 1 if ASTDT >= TR01SDT, or Set to ASTDT - TR01SDT if ASTDT < TR01SDT
AENDT Analysis End Date integer DATE9.
Derived
Converted date part of CM.CMENDTC to numeric if day, month, and year are all present If day and month are both missing, AENDT is whichever is earliest of the following: 31DECYYYY, EOSDT, or DTHDT If only day is missing, AENDT is whichiever is earliest of the following: EOSDT, DTHDT, or xxMMMYYYY where xx is the last day of the month
AENDTF Analysis End Date Imputation Flag text 1
Derived
Set to 'D' if only the day is imputed, or Set to 'M' if the day and the month are imputed
AENDY Analysis End Relative Day integer 8
Derived
Set to AENDT - TR01SDT + 1 if AENDT >= TR01SDT, or Set to AENDT - TR01SDT if AENDT < TR01SDT
MDOSREF Most Recent Dose Reference text 50
Derived
Set to 'Vaccination 1' if 1. missing < ADSL.TR01SDT <= ASTDT < ADSL.DOSE2DT or 2. missing < ADSL.TR01SDT <= ASTDT and ADSL.DOS2DT is missing and (ADSL.TR02SDT is missing or missing < ASTDT < ADSL.TR02SDT), Set to 'Vaccination 2' if 1. missing < ADSL.DOS2DT <= ASTDT < ADSL.TR02SDT or 2. missing < ADSL.DOS2DT <= ASTDT and ADSL.TR02SDT is missing, Set to 'OL Vaccination 1' if 1. missing < ADSL.TR02SDT <= ASTDT<ADSL.OLDOS2DT or 2. missing < ADSL.TR02SDT <= ASTDT and ADSL.OLDOS2DT is missing, Set to 'OL Vaccination 2' if missing < ADSL.OLDOS2DT <= ASTDT
APERIOD Period integer 8
Derived
Set to 2 if ASTDTM>=ADSL.TR02SDTM (or ASTDT>=ADSL.AP02SSDT if ASTDTM or TR02SDTM has time part missing), otherwise, Set to 1

Derived

Methods

Methods
Method Type Description
ADUREDT Computation
First set to AENDT, then if 1) missing, set to the earlier of (cutoff date, non missing ADSL.EOSDT) 2) if partial AENDT: If only day is missing, set to the earlier of (the last date of that month, cutoff date, non missing ADSL.EOSDT) If both month and day are missing, set to the earlier of (the last date of the yeatr, cutoff date, non missing ADSL.EOSDT)
ADURN Computation
For records where SMQ01FL - SMQ14FL='Y' or ARTERM is not missing, do the following: per SUBJID per AEDECOD per MDOSREF, calculate the duration days: ADUREDT-ADURSDT+1 if there are multiple events, sum the duration of each event excluding the overlapping periods
ADURSDT Computation
Set to ASTDT if ASTDT is not missing, Set to TR01SDT if TRTEMFL='Y'
AECVDIAG Computation
Set to SUPPAE.QVAL where QNAM='AECVDIAG'
AEDISFL Computation
Set to 'Y' if either of the two conditions below is met: 1) If subject with DS.DSDECOD countians 'SERIOUS ADVERSE EVENT' or 'ADVERSE EVENT' and the specified adverse event number (numeric part of SUPPDS.QVAL where SUPPDS.QNAM='AESPIDX') match the numeric part of AE.AEGRPID where DSCAT = DISPOSITION EVENT and DS.DSSCAT='END OF STUDY' 2). If subject has record with AEOUT='FATAL' or AETERM contains 'DEATH'
AEHENDTC Computation
Set to SUPPAE.QVAL where QNAM='AEHOSPEN'
AEHSTDTC Computation
Set to SUPPAE.QVAL where QNAM='AEHOSPST'
AEMAFL Computation
Set to SUPPAE.QVAL where SUPPAE.QNAM=MAAEFL
AENDT Computation
Converted date part of AEENDTC to numeric
AENDTM Computation
Concatenate AENDT and AENTM if both are non-missing
AENTM Computation
Converted time part of AEENDTC to numeric
AEOUTSP Computation
Set to SUPPAE.QVAL where SUPPAE.QNAM=AEOUTSP
AESOFL Computation
Set to 'Y' if ARTERM is not missing
ANL01FL Computation
Set to Y if all the conditions below are met: 1) ARTERM in ('Pain', 'Erythema', 'Swelling', 'Underarm Gland Swelling or Tenderness'), 2) MRDSTDY>=8
ANL02FL Computation
Set to 'Y' if ANL01FL='Y' and: MRDSTDY=8 and it exists in SDTM.FACE where FATPTNUM=7 by SUBJID, MDOSREF/FATPTREF, ARTERM/FAOBJ
ANL03FL Computation
Set to 'Y' if all the conditions below are met: 1) ANL01FL='Y' 2) It exists in SDTM.FACE by SUBJID, MDOSREF/FATPTREF, ARTERM/FAOBJ. That is, subject's events happen in the same period in SDTM.FACE, link ADAE and SDTM.FACE by SUBJID, match the events and corresponding period by ADAE.MDOSREF=FACE.FATPTREF, and ADAE.ARTERM=FACE.FAOBJ 3) If MRDSTDY = 8, the event identified in FACE in step 2) should have max(FATPTNUM) < 7 4) It does not exist in FAAE by SUBJID - MDOSREF/FATPTREF - ARTERM/FAOBJ. Similar linking rule as in Step 2
ANL04FL Computation
Set to 'Y' if all the conditions below are met: 1) ANL01FL='Y' 2) It does not exist in FACE by SUBJID - MDOSREF/FATPTREF - ARTERM/FAOBJ
APERIOD Computation
Set to 2 if ASTDTM>=ADSL.TR02SDTM (or ASTDT>=ADSL.AP02SSDT if ASTDTM or TR02SDTM has time part missing), otherwise, Set to 1
APLFL Computation
Subject level flag based on import.SMQ where SMQNAME='ANAPHYLACTIC REACTION': Set to 'Y' if one of the conditions below is met: 1) AEDECOD in import.SMQ where SMQ.Scope='Narrow' or SMQ.Category = 'A' 2) One AEDECOD in import.SMQ where SMQ.Category = 'B' and One AEDECOD in import.SMQ where SMQ.Category = 'C'. The two identified events should occur within 24 hours based on AESTDTC 3) One AEDECOD in import.SMQ where SMQ.Category = 'D' and [One AEDECOD in import.SMQ where SMQ.Category = 'B' or One AEDECOD in import.SMQ where SMQ.Category = 'C]. The two identified events should occur within 24 hours based on AESTDTC. Note: Use date part to compare if time part is missing, and no date or time imputation
APLREAS Computation
Refer to the 3 conditions for APLFL: If condition 1 is met, APLREAS = "A narrow term or a term from Category A", If condition 2 is met, APLREAS = "A term from Category B and a term from Category C ", If condition 3 is met, APLREAS = "A term from Category D and [a term from Category B or a term from Category C] " Note: If multiple reasons, concatenate and seperate by '; '
AREL Computation
Set to AEREL
ASEV Computation
Concatenate ATOXGR and Mixed case of AESEV with '/', eg, Grade 1/Mild; Set to ATOXGR if ATOXGR is 'Grade 4' or 'Grade 5'
ASTAGE Computation
Set to 'Vaccination stage' if (.< ADSL.TR01SDTM <=ASTDTM and ASTDT<= ADSL.TR01EDT+27) or (.< ADSL.TR02SDTM <=ASTDTM and ASTDT<= ADSL.TR02EDT+27), Note: If time part of TR01SDTM or time part of ASTDTM is missing,then use TR01SDT and ASTDT, if time part of TR02SDTM or time part of ASTDTM is missing, then use TR02SDT and ASTDT Set to 'Follow-Up stage' if (APERIOD=1 and ASTDT> ADSL.TR01EDT+27) or ASTDT> ADSL.TR02EDT+27
ASTDT Computation
Convert date part of AESTDTC convert to numeric See ADAE.ASTDT from ADaM Variable definition doc. for the date imputation rule

Additional ADaM Variable Definition

ASTDTF Computation
Set to 'M' if year is present and month is imputed, or Set to 'D' if only day is imputed
ASTDTM Computation
Concatenate ASTDT and ASTTM if both are non-missing
ASTDY Computation
Set to ASTDT – ADSL.TR01SDT + 1 if ASTDT >= TR01SDT Set to ASTDT – ADSL.TR01SDT if ASTDT< TR01SDT
ATOXGR Computation
Set to 'Grade 1' if AETOXGR='1', Set to 'Grade 2’ if AETOXGR='2', Set to ‘Grade 3’ if AETOXGR='3', Set to ‘Grade 4’ if AETOXGR='4', Set to ‘Grade 5’ if AEOUT='FATAL' or AETERM contains 'DEATH'
CMQ01FL Computation
Set ''Y' if CQ01NAM is not missing
CQ01NAM Computation
Set to 'Autoimmune' if AEDECOD is in import.CMQ where CMQNAME='AUTOIMMUNE'
CMQ01FL Computation
Set ''Y' if CQ02NAM is not missing
CQ01NAM Computation
Set to 'Dermal Filler Reaction Post Vaccination' if AEDECOD is in import.CMQ where CMQNAME='DERMAL FILLER REACTION POST VACCINATION'
CMQ03FL Computation
Y' if CQ03NAM is not missing
CQ03NAM Computation
Set to 'Bell's Palsy' if AELLT is in ('Bell's palsy', 'Palsy Bells', 'Facial palsy', and 'Facial paralysis')
D28FL Computation
Set to 'Y' if non-missing MRDSTDY<=28
ICUAD Computation
Set to HO.HOOCCUR where HODECOD='ICU' based on SUPPAE.QVAL where QNAM='HOSPIDX' and SUPPHO.QVAL where QNAM='HOSPIDX'
ICUDAY Computation
Set to HO.HODUR where HODECOD='ICU' based on SUPPAE.QVAL where QNAM='HOSPIDX' and SUPPHO.QVAL where QNAM='HOSPIDX'
MDOSREF Computation
Set to 'Vaccination 1' if (missing < ADSL.TR01SDTM <= ASTDTM < ADSL.DOSE2DTM) or ( missing < ADSL.TR01SDTM <= ASTDTM and ADSL.DOSE2DTM is missing and (TR02SDTM is missing or missing < ASTDTM < ADSL.TR02SDTM)) Set to 'Vaccination 2' if ( missing < ADSL.DOS2DTM <= ASTDTM < ADSL.TR02SDTM) or ( missing < ADSL.DOS2DTM <= ASTDTM and ADSL.TR02SDTM is missing) Set to 'OL Vaccination 1' if ( missing <ADSL.TR02SDTM <= ASTDTM < ADSL.OLDO2DTM) or ( missing < ADSL.TR02SDTM <= ASTDTM and ADSL.OLDO2DTM is missing) Set to 'OL Vaccination 2' if missing < ADSL.OLDO2DTM <= ASTDTM Note: Using date variables for comparison when time part is not available
MRDENDY Computation
Set to (the largest integer less than or equal to (AENDTM – ADSL.TR01SDTM)/(24*60*60)) + 1 if MDOSREF='Vaccination 1', Set to (the largest integer less than or equal to (AENDTM – ADSL.DOS2DTM)/(24*60*60)) + 1 if MDOSREF='Vaccination 2', Set to (the largest integer less than or equal to (AENDTM – ADSL.TR02SDTM)/(24*60*60)) + 1 If MDOSREF='OL Vaccination 1', Set to (the largest integer less than or equal to (AENDTM – ADSL.OLDO2DTM)/(24*60*60)) + 1 If MDOSREF='OL Vaccination 2' If time part of AENDTM is missing, use AENDT to replace AEENDTM and calculate as follows: AENDT – ADSL.TR01SDT+ 1 If MDOSREF='Vaccination 1', AENDT – ADSL.DOSE2DT+ 1 If MDOSREF='Vaccination 2', AENDT – ADSL.TR02SDT+ 1 If MDOSREF='OL Vaccination 1', AENDT – ADSL.OLDOS2DT+ 1 If MDOSREF='OL Vaccination 2'
MRDSTDY Computation
Set to (the largest integer less than or equal to (ASTDTM – ADSL.TR01SDTM)/(24*60*60)) +1 if MDOSREF='Vaccination 1', Set to (the largest integer less than or equal to (ASTDTM – ADSL.DOS2DTM)/(24*60*60)) +1 if MDOSREF='Vaccination 2,' Set to (the largest integer less than or equal to (ASTDTM – ADSL.TR02SDTM)/(24*60*60)) +1 if MDOSREF='OL Vaccination 1', Set to (the largest integer less than or equal to (ASTDTM – ADSL.OLDO2DTM)/(24*60*60)) +1 if MDOSREF='OL Vaccination 2' Note: If time part of ASTDTM is missing, use ASTDT to replace ASTDTM and calculate as follows: Set to ASTDT – ADSL.TR01SDT + 1 if MDOSREF='Vaccination 1', Set to ASTDT – ADSL.DOSE2DT + 1 if MDOSREF='Vaccination 2', Set to ASTDT – ADSL.TR02SDT + 1 if MDOSREF='OL Vaccination 1', Set to ASTDT – ADSL.OLDOS2DT + 1 if MDOSREF='OL Vaccination 2'
SMQ01FL Computation
Set to 'Y' if SMQ01NAM is not missing
SMQ01NAM Computation
Set to 'Anaphylactic Reaction' if AEDECOD is in import.SMQ where SMQNAME='ANAPHYLACTIC REACTION'
SMQ01SC Computation
Set to SMQ.SCOPE if AEDECOD is in import.SMQ where SMQNAME='ANAPHYLACTIC REACTION'
SMQ02FL Computation
Set to 'Y' if SMQ02NAM is not missing and SMQ02SC is 'Narrow'
SMQ02NAM Computation
Set to 'Angioedema' if AEDECOD is in import.SMQ where SMQNAME='ANGIOEDEMA'

SMQ09SC Computation

SMQ10FL Computation

SMQ14SC Computation
Set to SMQ.SCOPE if AEDECOD is in import.SMQ where SMQNAME='CARDIOMYOPATHY'
TOXGGR1 Computation
Pooled grouping of toxicity grade for analysis: Set to '<3' when .<ATOXGRN <3, or Set to '>=3' when ATOXGRN >=3
TRTA Computation
If MDOSREF='Vaccination 1', set to: 'Placebo' if EX.EXTRT='PLACEBO' where EX.VISIT contains 'Day 1', 'mRNA-1273' if EX.EXTRT='mRNA-1273' where EX.VISIT contains 'Day 1', if MDOSREF='Vaccination 2', set to: 'Placebo' if EX.EXTRT='PLACEBO' where EX.VISIT contains 'Day 29', 'mRNA-1273' if EX.EXTRT='mRNA-1273' where EX.VISIT contains 'Day 29', If MDOSREF='OL Vaccination 1', set to: 'Placebo' if EX.EXTRT='PLACEBO' where EX.VISIT contains 'OL-D1', 'mRNA-1273' if EX.EXTRT='mRNA-1273' where EX.VISIT contains 'OL-D1', if MDOSREF='OL Vaccination 2', set to: 'Placebo' if EX.EXTRT='PLACEBO' where EX.VISIT contains 'OL-D29', 'mRNA-1273' if EX.EXTRT='mRNA-1273' where EX.VISIT contains 'OL-D29'
TRTEMFL Computation
Set to 'Y' if .< ADSL.TR01SDTM <= ASTDTM, or (if ASTDT missing and .< ADSL.TR01SDTM <= AENDTM) or both ASTDT and AENDT missing. Note: If time is not available, use TR01SDT, ASTDT and AENDT
ADT Computation
Convert date part of FACE.FADTC to numeric if source data are from FACE Convert date part of VS.VSDTC to numeric if source data are from VS
ADTM Computation
Convert FACE.FADTC to numeric if source data are from FACE Convert VS.VSDTC to numeric if source data are from VS
ADY Computation
Set to FACE.FADY if source data are from FACE Set to VS.VSDY if source data are from VS
ANL01FL Computation
Set 'Y' for the first record with maximum non-missing ATOXGRN per subject per PARAM per vaccination (ATPTREF) per ATPTGR1 Note: If there are two or more records found, then select the first one where FAEVAL='STUDY SUBJECT' or missing for FEVER
ANL02FL Computation
Y for the records where PARAMCD is 'PAIN' or 'ERYTHDIA' or 'SWELLDIA', and ATOXGRN>0
ANL03FL Computation
Y for the first record with maximum non-missing ATOXGRN per subject per PARAM per vaccination (ATPTREF) per ATPT Note: If there are two or more records found, then select the first one where FAEVAL='STUDY SUBJECT' or missing for FEVER
ARTERM Computation
Set to import.symp.CETERM where ADAE.AEDECOD = import.symp.CEDECOD
ATPT Computation
If source data are from FACE, set to FACE.FATPT, otherwise If source data are from VS, set to VS.VSTPT Recode 'DAY 1' as 'DAY 1, AFTER VACCINATION (AT HOME)' if FAEVAL='INVESTIGATOR''
ATPTGR1 Computation
Set to 'Day 1' if ATPT contains 'Day 1' Set to ATPT otherwise
ATPTREF Computation
If source data are from FACE Set to ‘Vaccination 1’ if FACE.FATPTREF contains ‘DOSE1’ Set to ‘Vaccination 2’ if FACE.FATPTREF contains ‘DOSE2’ If source data are from VS Set to 'Vaccination 1' if VS.VSTPTREF contatins 'DOSE1', Set to 'Vaccination 2' if VS.VSTPTREF contains 'DOSE2'
AVALC Computation
Set to FACE.FASTRESC if source data are from FACE, Set to VS.VSSTRESC if source data are from VS
FAVER Computation
Set to VS.VSSTRESN if source data are from VS
ERYTHDIA, SWELLDIA Computation
For FACE.FAOBJ = ’Erythema’ or ‘Swelling’ only Set to 0 if FATEST='Occurrence Indicator' and FAORRES='N', otherwise Set to FACE.FASTRESN
OTHER Computation
Set to missing
CRIT1 Computation
Set to '> 102.6 degrees F' if CRIT1FL='Y'
CRIT1FL Computation
Set to 'Y' if (9*AVAL/5)+32 > 102.6
CRIT2 Computation
Set to '> 103.1 degrees F' if CRIT2FL='Y'
CRIT2FL Computation
Set to 'Y' if (9*AVAL/5)+32 > 103.1
CRIT3 Computation
Set to '> 103.6 degrees F' if CRIT3FL='Y'
CRIT3FL Computation
Set to 'Y' if (9*AVAL/5)+32 > 103.6
CRIT4 Computation
Set to '> 104.1 degrees F' if CRIT4FL='Y'
CRIT4FL Computation
Set to 'Y' if (9*AVAL/5)+32 > 104.1
MAAEFL Computation
Set to SUPPFACE.QVAL where SUPPFACE.QNAM='MAAEFL'
ADT Computation
Convert date part of FACE.FADTC to numeric if source data are from FACE Convert date part of FAAE.FADTC to numeric if source data are from FAAE Convert date part of VS.VSDTC to numeric if source data are from VS
ADTM Computation
Convert FACE.FADTC to numeric if source data are from FACE Convert FAAE.FADTC to numeric if source data are from FAAE Convert VS.VSDTC to numeric if source data are from VS
ADY Computation
Set to FACE.FADY if source data are from FACE Set to FAAE.FADY if source data are from FAAE Set to VS.VSDY if source data are from VS
ANL01FL Computation
Set to 'Y' for the records where PARAMCD is 'PAIN' or 'ERYTHDIA' or 'SWELLDIA', or 'LYMPH'
ANL02FL Computation
If ANL01FL=Y, per subject per vaccination per symptom, flag all records if there are records at both ATPTN = 7 and ATPTN = 8
ANL03FL Computation
If ANL01FL=Y, per subject per vaccination per symptom with min(ATPTN) <=7, flag all records if there are not records at both ATPTN = 7 and ATPTN = 8
ANL04FL Computation
Set to 'Y' for the records if both criteria met: 1. ANL01FL='Y', 2. If per subject per symptom (PARAMCD) per vaccination (ATPTREF), the smallest ATPTGR1N >=8
ANL05FL Computation
Set to 'Y' for the first record with maximum non-missing ATOXGRN per subject per PARAM per vaccination (ATPTREF) per ATPT Note: If there is two records per day and one from investigator and one from subject, select the one from subject (FAEVAL='STUDY SUBJECT' or missing FAEVAL for FEVER)
ANL06FL Computation
Per subject per vaccination per symptom, flag all records if the smallest ATPTGR1N<8 and largest ATPTGR1N>=8 where ATOXGRN>0
ATPT Computation
If source data are from FACE, set to FACE.FATPT If Source data are from FAAE, set to FAAE.FATPT If source data are from VS, set to VS.VSTPT Recode 'DAY 1' as 'DAY 1, AFTER VACCINATION (AT HOME)' if FAEVAL='INVESTIGATOR''
ATPTREF Computation
If source data are from FACE Set to ‘Vaccination 1’ if FACE.FATPTREF contains ‘DOSE1’ Set to ‘Vaccination 2’ if FACE.FATPTREF contains ‘DOSE2’ If source data are from FAAE Set to ‘Vaccination 1’ if FAAE.FATPTREF contains ‘DOSE1’ Set to ‘Vaccination 2’ if FAAE.FATPTREF contains ‘DOSE2’ If source data are from VS Set to 'Vaccination 1' if VS.VSTPTREF contains 'DOSE1', Set to 'Vaccination 2' if VS.VSTPTREF contains 'DOSE2'
AVALC1 Computation
Set to SUPPVS.QVAL if SUPPVS.QNAM in ('MEDTAK', 'MEDTAKP', 'MEDTAKT') and QVAL='Y'
AVALC2 Computation
Set to FACE.FASTRESC If data is from SDTM.FACE, Set to FAAE.FASTRESC If data is from SDTM.FAAE, Set to VS.VSSTRESC If data is from VS
FEVER Computation
If a subject has a least one record found from SDTM.VS where VSCAT="REACTOGENICITY" and VSTPTNUM>=8, then Set to VS.VSSTRESN where VSCAT='REACTOGENICITY'
ERYTHDIA, SWELLDIA Computation
If data is from SDTM.FACE[1] Set to FACE.FASTRESN where FACE.FAOBJ in ('Erythema', 'Swelling') and FATESTCD='LDIAM' If data is from SDTM.FAAE Set to FAAE.FASTRESN where FAAE.FAOBJ in ('Erythema', 'Swelling') and FAAE.FATESTCE='LDIAM' [1]A least one records should be found from SDTM.FAAE where FAAE.FAOBJ in ('Erythema', 'Swelling') and FATESTCD='LDIAM')
OTHER Computation
Set to missing
FAEVAL Computation
Set to FACE/FAAE.FAEVAL
MAAEFL Computation
Set to SUPPFACE/SUPPFAAE.QVAL where SUPPFACE/SUPPFAAE.QNAM='MAAEFL'
PARAM Computation
If source data are from FACE/FAAE: If FAOBJ=’Underarm Gland Swelling or Tenderness’ and FATESTCD = 'SEV', then set to FAOBJ, If FAOBJ=’Nausea/Vomiting’ and FATESTCD = 'SEV', then set to 'Nausea/Vomiting', If FAOBJ=’Erythema’ or ‘Swelling’ and FATEST contains 'Occurrence' and FAORRES='N', then set to FAOBJ||' Longest Diameter (mm)' and assign AVAL=0 (see specs for AVAL), If FAOBJ= ’Erythema’ or ‘Swelling’ and FATEST contains 'Intensity', then set to FAOBJ||' Longest Diameter (mm)', If FAOBJ=’ Erythema’ or ‘Swelling’ and FATEST='Longest Diameter', set to 'FAOBJ'|| ' '||FATEST|| ' '||'('||FAORRESU||')', If FAOBJ='Pyrexia' or 'Fever', then set to 'Fever (C)', set to FAOBJ, otherwise If source data are from VS and VSTESTCD in ('TEMP' 'VSALL'), set to 'Fever'||'('||VSSTRESU||'). (please add space between the VSTEST and VS unit. If the VSSTRESU is missing, use non-missing VSSTRESU)" If there is one record in VS where SUPPVS.QNAM='MEDTAKP' and QVAL='Y', then create one record with PARAM='Prevent Pain or Fever from Occurring', If there is one record in VS where SUPPVS.QNAM='MEDTAKT' and QVAL='Y', then create one record with PARAM='Treat Pain or Fever already Occurred', If there is one record in VS where SUPPVS.QNAM='MEDTAK' and QVAL='Y', then create one record with PARAM='Medication Taken Today for Pain or Fever'
PARAM Computation
If source data are from FACE: If FAOBJ=’Underarm Gland Swelling or Tenderness’ and FATESTCD = 'SEV', then set to 'Underarm Gland Swelling or Tenderness' If FAOBJ=’Nausea/Vomiting’ and FATESTCD = 'SEV', then set to 'Nausea/Vomiting'' If FAOBJ=’Erythema’ or ‘Swelling’ and FATEST contains 'Occurrence' and FAORRES='N', then set to FAOBJ||' Longest Diameter (mm)' and assign AVAL=0 (see specs for AVAL) If FAOBJ= ’Erythema’ or ‘Swelling’ and FATEST contains 'Intensity', then set to FAOBJ||' Longest Diameter (mm)' If FAOBJ=’ Erythema’ or ‘Swelling’ and FATEST='Longest Diameter', set to 'FAOBJ'|| ' '||FATEST|| ' '||'('||FAORRESU||')' If FAOBJ='Pyrexia' or 'Fever', then set to 'Fever (C)' set to FAOBJ, otherwise if source data are from VS and VSTESTCD in ('TEMP' 'VSALL'), set to 'Fever'||'('||VSSTRESU||'). (please add space between the VSTEST and VS unit. If the VSSTRESU is missing, use non-missing VSSTRESU) if there is one record in VS where SUPPVS.QNAM='MEDTAKP' and QVAL='Y', then create one record with PARAM='Prevent Pain or Fever from Occurring'; if there is one record in VS where SUPPVS.QNAM='MEDTAKT' and QVAL='Y', then create one record with PARAM='Treat Pain or Fever already Occurred'; if there is one record in VS where SUPPVS.QNAM='MEDTAK' and QVAL='Y', then create one record with PARAM='Medication Taken Today for Pain or Fever'.
PARCAT1 Computation
For source data are from SDTM.FACE/FAAE: Set to 'LOCAL' if FASCAT=ADMINISTRATION SITE Set to FASCAT For source data are from VS: Set to VSSCAT
SRCDOM Computation
FACE.DOMAIN if source data are from FACE; VS.DOMAIN if source data are from VS
SRCSEQ Computation
FACE.FASEQ if source data are from FACE; VS.VSSEQ if source data are from VS
SRCVAR Computation
Set to 'FASTRESC' if source data are from FACE; Set to 'VSSTRESN' if source data are from VS; Set to "SUPPVS.QVAL where QNAM='MEDTAKP'" if PARAMCD='MEDTAKP'; else set to "SUPPVS.QVAL where QNAM='MEDTAKT'" if PARAMCD='MEDTAKT'; else set to "SUPPVS.QVAL where QNAM='MEDTAK'" if PARAMCD='MEDTAK'.
ANL01FL Computation
Set to 'Y' for the records that met either of below criteria: 1. ADARSUM.PARAMCD is 'PAINDUR', for the same subject and same vaccination (ATPTREF), the smallest ADARP7D.ATPTGR1N>=8 where ADARP7D.PARAMCD='PAIN' and ATOXGRN>0 2. ADARSUM.PARAMCD is 'ERYTHDUR', for the same subject and same vaccination (ATPTREF), the smallest ADARP7D.ATPTGR1N>=8 where ADARP7D.PARAMCD='ERYTHDIA' and ATOXGRN>0 3. ADARSUM.PARAMCD is 'SWELLDUR', for the same subject and same vaccination (ATPTREF), the smallest ADARP7D.ATPTGR1N>=8 where ADARP7D.PARAMCD='SWELLDIA' and ATOXGRN>0
ANL02FL Computation
Set to 'Y' if PARAMCD in (PAINDUR, ERYTHDUR, SWELLDUR, HEADADUR, LYMPHDUR, FATIGDUR, MYALGDUR, ARTHRDUR, NAUSEDUR, CHILLDUR, FEVERDUR, ANYDUR, LOCDUR, SYSDUR) and no corresponded symptom last beyond day 7 (no any record is found from ADARP7D by ATPTREF)
ATOXGR Computation
Set to the highest ATOXGR by subject, ADAR.PARAMCD, and vaccination (ATPTREF)
ATOXGRANY Computation
Set to the highest ATOXGR by subject, and vaccination (ATPTREF)
ATOXGRG Computation
Set to the highest ATOXGR by subject, ADAR.PARCAT1, and vaccination (ATPTREF)
ATPTREF Computation
Set to ADAR.ATPTREF if data from ADAR For source data from FAAE: Set to ‘Vaccination 1’ if FAAE.FATPTREF contains ‘DOSE 1’, or Set to ‘Vaccination 2’ if FAAE.FATPTREF contains ‘DOSE 2’ For source data from VS, Set to ‘Vaccination 1’ if VS.VSTPTREF contains ‘DOSE 1’, or Set to ‘Vaccination 2’ if VS.VSTPTREF contains ‘DOSE 2’
AVAL Computation
1. Get number of days from ADAR: Count total number of records with ATOXGRN>0 per subject, per symptom (ADAR.PARAMCD) and per vaccination (ATPTREF). If there are more than one record within same day (ADAR.ATPTGR1), then count it once only 2. Get number of days from ADARP7D: Count total number of records with ATOXGRN>0 and ADAR.P7D.ATPTGR1N>=8 per subject, per symptom (ADARP7D.PARAMCD) and per vaccination (ATPTREF). If there are more than one record within same day (ADARP7D.ATPTGR1), then count it once only 3. Calculate the sum of the number of records from steps 1 and 2 per subject per, per symptom (PARAMCD) and per vaccination (ATPTREF)
AVAL Any Computation
1. Get number of days from ADAR: Count total number of records with ATOXGRN>0 per subject and per vaccination (ATPTREF). If there are more than one record within same day (ADAR.ATPTGR1), then count it once only 2. Get number of days from ADARP7D: Count total number of records with ATOXGRN>0 and ADARP7D.ATPTGR1N>=8 per subject and per vaccination (ATPTREF). If there are more than one record within same day (ADARP7D.ATPTGR1), then count it once only 3. Calculate the sum of the number of records from steps 1 and 2 per subject per and per vaccination (ATPTREF)
AVALC Computation
Derived worse case of each AR symptom occurred within 7 days per vaccination (ATPTREF) where PARAMCD in (WLYMPH, WPAIN, WERYTH, WSWELL, WHEAD, WFATIGUE, WMYALGIA, WARTHR, WNAUSEA, WCHILLS, WFEVER): Set to ADAR.AVALC where ADAR.ATOXGR is the worse case per AR symptom within 7 Days per vaccination (ATPTREF) Note: The higher number of ADAR.ATOXGRN, the worse symptom grade
AVALG Computation
1. Get number of days from ADAR: Count total number of records with ATOXGRN>0 per subject, per symptom category (ADAR.PARCAT1) and per vaccination (ATPTREF). If there are more than one record within same day (ADAR.ATPTGR1), then count it once only 2. Get number of days from ADARP7D: Count total number of records with ATOXGRN>0 and ADARP7D.ATPTGR1N>=8 per subject, per symptom category (ADARP7D.PARCAT1) and per vaccination (ATPTREF). If there are more than one record within same day (ADARP7D.ATPTGR1), then count it once only 3. Calculate the sum of the number of records from steps 1 and 2 per subject per, per symptom (PACAT1) and per vaccination (ATPTREF)
PARAM Computation
Create one PARAM per subject per PARCAT1 per ATPTREF by following Solicited AR Summary Analysis Dataset Parameter Code
PARCAT1 Computation
Set to 'LOCAL' if PARAMCD in (LYMPHDUR, PAINDUR, ERYTHDUR, SWELLDUR, WLYMPH, WPAIN, WERYTH, WSWELL, WSLAR) Set to 'SYSTEMIC' if PARAMCD in (HEADADUR, FATIGDUR, MYALGDUR ARTHRDUR, NAUSEDUR, CHILLDUR, FEVERDUR, WHEAD, WFATIGUE, WMYALGIA, WARTHR, WNAUSEA, WCHILLS,WFEVER, WSSAR)
PARAMCD EQ CHILLS Computation
Set to 'Grade 0' if FASTRESC=’NONE’ or contains 'GRADE 0' Set to 'Grade 1' if FASTRESC= ‘NO INTERFERENCE WITH ACTIVITY’ or contains 'GRADE 1' Set to 'Grade 2' if FASTRESC= ‘SOME INTERFERENCE WITH ACTIVITY NOT REQUIRING MEDICAL ATTENTION’ or contains 'GRADE 2' Set to 'Grade 3' if FASTRESC= ‘PREVENTS DAILY ACTIVITY AND REQUIRES MEDICAL ATTENTION’ or contains 'GRADE 3' Set to 'Grade 4' if FASTRESC contains 'GRADE 4'
ERYTHDIA and SWELLDIA Computation
Set to 'Grade 0' if .<AVAL < 25 mm or FASTRESC contains 'GRADE 0' Set to 'Grade 1' if AVAL = 25 - 50 mm or FASTRESC contains 'GRADE 1' Set to 'Grade 2' if AVAL = 51 - 100 mm or FASTRESC contains 'GRADE 2' Set to 'Grade 3' if AVAL > 100 mm or FASTRESC contains 'GRADE 3' Set to 'Grade 4' if FASTRESC contains 'GRADE 4'
PARAMCD EQ FEVER Computation
Grade 0 if .<AVAL < 38.0°C or FASTRESC contains 'GRADE 0' Grade 1 if 38.0<=AVAL<=38.4°C or FASTRESC contains 'GRADE 1' Grade 2 if 38.4<AVAL<=38.9°C or FASTRESC contains 'GRADE 2' Grade 3 if 38.9<AVAL<=40.0°C or FASTRESC contains 'GRADE 3' Grade 4 if AVAL > 40.0°C or FASTRESC contains 'GRADE 4'
FATIGUE, MYALGIA, ARTHRALG) Computation
Set to 'Grade 0' if FASTRESC=’NONE’ or contains 'GRADE 0' Set to 'Grade 1' if FASTRESC= 'NO INTERFERENCE WITH ACTIVITY' or contains 'GRADE 1' Set to 'Grade 2' if FASTRESC= ‘SOME INTERFERENCE WITH ACTIVITY’ or contains 'GRADE 2' Set to 'Grade 3' if FASTRESC= ‘SIGNIFICANT; PREVENTS DAILY ACTIVITY’ or contains 'GRADE 3' Grade 4 if FASTRESC contains 'GRADE 4'
PARAMCD EQ HEADACHE Computation
Set to 'Grade 0' if FASTRESC=’NONE’ or contains 'GRADE 0' Set to 'Grade 1' if FASTRESC=’NO INTERFERENCE WITH ACTIVITY’ or contains 'GRADE 1' Set to 'Grade 2' if FASTRESC= ‘REPEATED USE OF OVER-THE-COUNTER PAIN RELIEVER > 24 HOURS OR SOME INTERFERENCE WITH ACTIVITY’ or contains 'GRADE 2'; Set to 'Grade 3' if FASTRESC= ‘ANY USE OF PRESCRIPTION PAIN RELIEVER OR PREVENTS DAILY ACTIVITY’ or contains 'GRADE 3' Set to 'Grade 4' if FASTRESC contains 'GRADE 4'
PARAMCD EQ LYMPH Computation
Set to 'Grade 0' if FASTRESC=’NONE’ or contains 'GRADE 0' Set to 'Grade 1' if FASTRESC=’DOES NOT INTERFERE WITH ACTIVITY’ or contains 'GRADE 1' Set to 'Grade 2' if FASTRESC= ‘REPEATED USE OF OVER-THE-COUNTER PAIN RELIEVER > 24 HOURS OR INTERFERES WITH SOME ACTIVITY’ or contains 'GRADE 2' Set to 'Grade 3' if FASTRESC= ‘ANY USE OF PRESCRIPTION PAIN RELIEVER OR PREVENTS DAILY ACTIVITY’ or contains 'GRADE 3'; Set to 'Grade 4' if FASTRESC contains 'GRADE 4'
NAUSEA Computation
Set to 'Grade 0' if FASTRESC=’NONE’ or contains 'GRADE 0' Set to 'Grade 1' if FASTRESC= ‘NO INTERFERENCE WITH ACTIVITY OR 1-2 EPISODES/24 HOURS’ or contains 'GRADE 1' Set to 'Grade 2' if FASTRESC= ‘SOME INTERFERENCE WITH ACTIVITY OR >2 EPISODES/24 HOURS’ or contains 'GRADE 2' Set to 'Grade 3' if FASTRESC= ‘PREVENTS DAILY ACTIVITY, REQUIRES OUTPATIENT IV HYDRATION’ or contains 'GRADE 3' Set to 'Grade 4' if FASTRESC contains 'GRADE 4'
PARAM EQ PAIN Computation
Set to 'Grade 0' if FASTRESC=’NONE’ or contains 'GRADE 0' Set to 'Grade 1' if FASTRESC=’DOES NOT INTERFERE WITH ACTIVITY’ or contains 'GRADE 1' Set to 'Grade 2' if FASTRESC= ‘REPEATED USE OF OVER-THE-COUNTER PAIN RELIEVER > 24 HOURS OR INTERFERES WITH ACTIVITY’ or contains 'GRADE 2' Grade 3 if FASTRESC= ‘ANY USE OF PRESCRIPTION PAIN RELIEVER OR PREVENTS DAILY ACTIVITY’ or contains 'GRADE 3'; Set to 'Grade 4' if FASTRESC contains 'GRADE 4'
AENDT Computation
Converted date part of CM.CMENDTC to numeric if day, month, and year are all present If day and month are both missing, AENDT is whichever is earliest of the following: 31DECYYYY, EOSDT, or DTHDT If only day is missing, AENDT is whichiever is earliest of the following: EOSDT, DTHDT, or xxMMMYYYY where xx is the last day of the month
AENDTF Computation
Set to 'D' if only the day is imputed, or Set to 'M' if the day and the month are imputed
AENDY Computation
Set to AENDT - TR01SDT + 1 if AENDT >= TR01SDT, or Set to AENDT - TR01SDT if AENDT < TR01SDT
ASTDT Computation
Convert date part of CM.CMSTDTC to numeric if day, month, and year are all present See ADCM.ASTDT from Additional ADaM Variable Definition Doc for partial date imputation rules

Additional ADaM Variable Definition

ASTDTF Computation
Set to 'D' if only the day is imputed, or Set to 'M' if the day and the month are imputed
ASTDY Computation
Set to ASTDT - TR01SDT + 1 if ASTDT >= TR01SDT, or Set to ASTDT - TR01SDT if ASTDT < TR01SDT
ATCLEV1T Computation
Set to SUPPCM.QVAL where QNAM='ATCLEV1T'
ATCLEV2T Computation

CMDECOD2 Computation

Y' if SUPPCM.QVAL='Y' where  QNAM='CMPLX'
