Additional ADaM Variable Definition

PARAM Computation
See controlled terms. Create one PARAM per subject for all full analysis subjects (FASFL = 'Y')
STARTDT Computation
Set to ADSL.RANDDT if PARAMCD not in (TTCVDC9, TCVDSVC9, TCVDSDC9, TTASYMP9, TTASYCR9, TTINF9, TTDTHCV9, TTDEATH9), Otherwise, Set to ADSL.AP02SDT
AVAL Computation
Derive based on the temporary variable SUM (see derivation of EVENTSEQ) and date of first symtom occure per subject (ADEFF3.ADT where FASYMPFL = 'Y') If SUM = 0 where EVENTSEQ = 1, set to the earliest date of (ADSL.DTHDT, ADSL.EOSDT, ADSL.CUTOFFDT) - TR01SDT. if 0 < SUM <= Q1 where EVENTSEQ = 1, set to the ADT - TR01SDT. if Q1 <= SUM < Median , then do: 1) if EVENTSEQ = 1, set to the ADT - TR01SDT. 2) if EVENTSEQ = 2, set to the ADT - TR01SDT + (1e-10). if Median <= SUM < Q3, then do: 1) if EVENTSEQ = 1, set to the ADT - TR01SDT. 2) if EVENTSEQ = 2, set to the ADT - TR01SDT + (1e-10). 3) if EVENTSEQ = 3, set to the ADT - TR01SDT + (2e-10). if Q3 <= SUM, then do: 1) if EVENTSEQ = 1, set to the ADT - TR01SDT. 2) if EVENTSEQ = 2, set to the ADT - TR01SDT + (1e-10). 3) if EVENTSEQ = 3, set to the ADT - TR01SDT + (2e-10). 4) if EVENTSEQ = 4, set to the ADT - TR01SDT + (3e-10).
CNSR Computation
If EVENTSEQ = 1, then do: 1) Set to 1 If temporary variable SUM (see derivation of EVENTSEQ) = 0, 2) Set to 0 If temporary variable SUM (see derivation of EVENTSEQ) > 0, if EVENTSEQ = 2 or 3 or 4, then set to 0 Note: (1 for censor; 0 for event)
EVENTSEQ Computation
Derive based on the records with ADEFF3.ANL01FL='Y' and PARCAT1N = 1 and PPROTFL = ’Y’. Step 1. Calculate temporary variable SUM = sum of AVAL per subject (SUBJID). Step 2. Calcalate min, max, Q1 and Q3 of SUM. Step 3. Assgin EVENTSEQ as follows: If SUM = 0 or 0 < SUM < Q1, assign one record/row with EVENTSEQ = 1; if Q1 <= SUM < Median, assign one record/row with EVENTSEQ = 1 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ = 2; if Median <= SUM < Q3, assign one record/row with EVENTSEQ = 1 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ = 2 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ = 3; if Q3 <= SUM, assign one record/row with EVENTSEQ = 1 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ = 2 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ = 3 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ = 4;
EVNTDESC Computation
For each USUBJID, Set to ‘No symptom’ if temporary variable SUM (see derivation of EVENTSEQ) = 0, Set to ‘0 < Total COVID-19 Symptoms Score < Q1’ if 0 < temporary variable SUM (see derivation of EVENTSEQ) < Q1, Set to ‘Q1 <= Total COVID-19 Symptoms Score < Median’ if Q1 <= temporary variable SUM (see derivation of EVENTSEQ) < Median, Set to ‘Median <= Total COVID-19 Symptoms Score < Q3’ if Median <= temporary variable SUM (see derivation of EVENTSEQ) < Q3, Set to ‘Q3 <= Total COVID-19 Symptoms Score’ if Q3 <= temporary variable SUM (see derivation of EVENTSEQ).
STARTVAL Computation
Derive based on the date of first symtom occure per subject (ADEFF3.ADT where FASYMPFL = 'Y') If EVENTSEQ = 1, set to 0. if EVENTSEQ = 2, set to the (ADT - ADSL.TR01SDT). if EVENTSEQ = 3, set to the (ADT - ADSL.TR01SDT) + (1e-10). if EVENTSEQ = 4, set to the (ADT - ADSL.TR01SDT) + (2e-10).
AVALD Computation
If where ADEFF2.PARAMCD contains 'BOD' : If ADEFF2.AVAL=0: Set to the earliest date of (ADSL.DTHDT, ADSL.EOSDT, ADSL.EFFCODT, ADSL.AP01EDT) - ADSL.RANDDT if and EVENTSEQ=1, Else: Set to the ADEFF2.ADT- ADSL.RANDDT where EVENTSEQ=1, Set to the ADEFF2.ADT- ADSL.RANDDT+(1e-10) where EVENTSEQ=2 Set to the ADEFF2.ADT- ADSL.RANDDT +(2e-10) where EVENTSEQ=3
AVALI Computation
Set to the earliest date of (ADSL.DTHDT, ADSL.EOSDT, ADSL.EFFCODT, ADSL.AP01EDT) - TR01SDT if ADEFF2.AVAL=0 and EVENTSEQ=1, Set to the ADEFF2.ADT- TR01SDT if EVENTSEQ=1, Set to the ADEFF2.ADT- TR01SDT +(1e-10) if EVENTSEQ=2, Set to the ADEFF2.ADT- TR01SDT +(2e-10) if EVENTSEQ=3, Set to the ADEFF2.ADT- TR01SDT +(3e-10) if EVENTSEQ=4, Set to the ADEFF2.ADT- TR01SDT +(4e-10) if EVENTSEQ=5, Set to the ADEFF2.ADT- TR01SDT +(5e-10) if EVENTSEQ=6
CNSRD Computation
If EVENTSEQ=1, then do: 1)Set to 1 If ADEFF2.AVAL=0 where PARAMCD contains 'BOD', 2)Set to 0 If ADEFF2.AVAL>=1 where PARAMCD contains 'BOD', If EVENTSEQ=2 or 3, then set to 0 Note: (1 for censor; 0 for event)
CNSRI Computation
If EVENTSEQ=1, then do: 1)Set to 1 If ADEFF2.AVAL=0 where PARAMCD contains 'BOI', 2)Set to 0 If ADEFF2.AVAL>=0.5 where PARAMCD contains 'BOI', If EVENTSEQ>=2, then set to 0 Note: (1 for censor; 0 for event)
EVENTSEQD Computation
Derive based on the records with ADEFF2.ANL01FL='Y': If ADEFF2.AVAL=0 or 1 where PARAMCD contains 'BOD', assign one record/row with EVENTSEQ=1, If ADEFF2.AVAL=2 where PARAMCD contains 'BOD', assign one record/row with EVENTSEQ=1 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ=2, If ADEFF2.AVAL=3 where PARAMCD contains 'BOD', assign one record/row with EVENTSEQ=1 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ=2 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ=3
EVENTSEQI Computation
Derive based on the records with ADEFF2.ANL01FL='Y': If ADEFF2.AVAL=0 or 0.5 where PARAMCD contains 'BOI', assign one record/row with EVENTSEQ=1, If ADEFF2.AVAL=1 where PARAMCD contains 'BOI', assign one record/row with EVENTSEQ=1 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ=2, If ADEFF2.AVAL=2 where PARAMCD contains 'BOI', assign one record/row with EVENTSEQ=1 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ=2 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ=3 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ=4, If ADEFF2.AVAL=3 where PARAMCD contains 'BOI', assign one record/row with EVENTSEQ=1 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ=2 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ=3 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ=4 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ=5 and one record/row with EVENTSEQ=6
EVNTDESCD Computation
For each USUBJID, Set to 'Without COVID-19' if ADEFF2.AVAL=0 where PARAMCD contains 'BOD', Set to 'COVID-19 without hospitalization' if ADEFF2.AVAL= 1 where PARAMCD contains 'BOD', Set to 'COVID-19 with hospitalization' if ADEFF2.AVAL=2 where PARAMCD contains 'BOD', Set to 'Death' if ADEFF2.AVAL=3 where PARAMCD contains 'BOD'
EVNTDESCI Computation
For each USUBJID, Set to 'No infection’ if ADEFF2.AVAL=0 where PARAMCD contains 'BOI', Set to 'Asymptomatic infection' if ADEFF2.AVAL=0.5 where PARAMCD contains 'BOI', Set to 'COVID-19 without hospitalization' if ADEFF2.AVAL=1 where PARAMCD contains 'BOI', Set to 'COVID-19 with hospitalization' if ADEFF2.AVAL=2 where PARAMCD contains 'BOI', Set to 'Death' if ADEFF2.AVAL=3 where PARAMCD contains 'BOI'
PARAM Computation
Create # of records based on ADEFF2.PARAMCD and ADEFF2.AVAL: Set to "Burden of Disease Score" if data is derived from ADEFF2.PARAMCD in (BOD7D, BOD28D) Set to 'Burden of Infection Score' if data is derived from ADEFF2.PARAMCD in (BOI7D, BOI28D)
STARTVALD Computation
Set to 0 if EVENTSEQ=1, Set to the (ADEFF2.ADT- ADSL.RANDDT) if EVENTSEQ=2, Set to the (ADEFF2.ADT- ADSL.RANDDT)+(1e-10) if EVENTSEQ=3
STARTVALI Computation
Set to 0 if EVENTSEQ=1, set to the (ADEFF2.ADT-ADSL.TR01SDT) if EVENTSEQ=2, Set to the (ADEFF2.ADT-ADSL.TR01SDT) +(1e-10) if EVENTSEQ=3, Set to the (ADEFF2.ADT-ADSL.TR01SDT) +(2e-10) if EVENTSEQ=4, Set to the (ADEFF2.ADT-ADSL.TR01SDT) +(3e-10) if EVENTSEQ=5, Set to the (ADEFF2.ADT-ADSL.TR01SDT) +(4e-10) if EVENTSEQ=6
ABLFL Computation
Set to 'Y' for the latest (consider both ADT and ATM) non-missing assessment (AVAL>. or non-missing AVALC) on or before TR01SDTM (TR01SDT if time part of TR01SDTM is missing) for each SUBJID and PARAMCD Note: exclude records where ADT is the same as TR01SDT and VSTPT^='PRE-DOSE'
ADT Computation
Convert date part of VS.VSDTC to numeric
ADTM Computation
Convert VS.VSDTC to numeric
ADY Computation
Set to ADT - ADSL.TR01SDT + 1 if ADT is on or after ADSL.TR01SDT, or Set to ADT - ADSL.TR01SDT if ADT is before ADSL.TR01SDT
ANL01FL Computation
If ABLFL='Y', then set to 'Y'; for post-baseline assessments where AVISITN is non-missing and result (AVAL) is non-missing, per subject per parameter and per AVISIT per ATPT, Within an AVISIT and ATPT, set to ‘Y’ for the assessment at scheduled visit (i.e., VISIT doesn't contain "UNSCHED"). If there are 2 or more assessments at same visit, set to the last assessment. If there is no scheduled visit, set to 'Y' for the assessment closest to the target study day (record with minimum AWTDIFF) in the visit window. If there are 2 or more assessments equal distance to the target study day (AWTDIFFs are same), set to the last assessment.
ANL02FL Computation
For post baseline records where PARAMCD in ('PULSE', 'SYSBP'), per subject per parameter per AVISIT per ATPT where AVISIT NE 'Baseline': Set to 'Y' for the worst toxicity grade (ATOXGRL) where ATOXDSCL is not missing using the following order: Grade 4> Grade 3>Grade 2>Grade 1>Grade 0. If there are more than one worst toxicity grades, then set to the first record
ANL03FL Computation
For post baseline records, per subject per parameter per AVISIT where AVISIT NE 'Baseline' Set to 'Y' for the worst toxicity grade (ATOXGRH) where ATOXDSCH is not missing using the following order: Grade 4> Grade 3>Grade 2>Grade 1>Grade 0.If there are more than one worst toxicity grades, then set to the first record
APERIOD Computation
Set to 2 if non-missing AP02SSDT<=ADT, Otherwise, Set to 1
ASTAGE Computation
Only derive for post baseline records where DOSE1FL='Y': For APERIOD=1: If DOSE2FL='Y' then set TEMP to date of VISIT 3 (i.e. SV.SVSTDTC where SV.VISIT = 'Visit 3 Day 57') else if DOSE2FL ne 'Y' then set TEMP to date of VISIT 2 (i.e. SV.SVSTDTC where SV.VISIT = 'Visit 2 Day 29') Then do following: set to ‘Vaccination stage’ If .< ADSL.TR01SDTM <=ADTM and ADT<=earliest date of (TEMP, ADSL.EOSDT, ADSL.DTHDT) Set to 'Follow-Up Analysis Period' if ADT > non-missing TEMP. If TEMP, ADSL.EOSDT, and ADSL.DTHDT are all unavailable, set to ‘Vaccination stage’ For APERIOD=2: If OLDOS2FL ='Y' then set TEMP to date of OL-Day57 (i.e. SV.SVSTDTC where SV.VISIT = 'OL-Day 57') else if OLDOS2FL ne 'Y' then set TEMP to date of OL-Day29 (i.e. SV.SVSTDTC where SV.VISIT = 'OL-Day 29') Then do following: set to ‘Vaccination stage’ If .< ADSL.TR02SDTM <=ADTM and ADT<=earliest date of (TEMP, ADSL.EOSDT, ADSL.DTHDT) Set to 'Follow-Up Analysis Period' if ADT > non-missing TEMP. If TEMP, ADSL.EOSDT, and ADSL.DTHDT are all unavailable, set to ‘Vaccination stage’ Else Set to missing
ATOXDSCH Computation
Set to: 'Fever' if PARAMCD = 'TEMP' 'Tachycardia' if PARAMCD = 'PULSE' 'Systolic Hypertension' if PARAMCD = 'SYSBP' 'Diastolic Hypertension' if PARAMCD = 'DIABP' 'Respiratory Rate Increased' if PARAMCD = 'RESP'
ATOXDSCL Computation
Set to 'Bradycardia' if PARAMCD = 'PULSE' Hypotension' if PARAMCD = 'SYSBP'
ATOXGRH Computation
Assign AVAL toxicity grading as follows If AVAL is not missing: Set to 'Grade 1' if 91 – 95 Set to 'Grade 2' if 96 – 100 Set to 'Grade 3' if >100 Grade 4 is based on medical input Otherwise, set to 'Grade 0'
ATOXGRH Computation
Assign AVAL toxicity grading as follows If AVAL is not missing: Set to 'Grade 1' if 101 – 115 Set to 'Grade 2' if 116 – 130 Set to 'Grade 3' if >130 Grade 4 is based on medical input Otherwise, set to 'Grade 0'
ATOXGRH Computation
Assign AVAL toxicity grading as follows If AVAL is not missing: Set to 'Grade 1' if 17 – 20 Set to 'Grade 2' if 21 – 25 Set to 'Grade 3' if >25 Grade 4 is based on medical input Otherwise, set to 'Grade 0'
ATOXGRH Computation
Assign AVAL toxicity grading as follows If AVAL is not missing: Set to 'Grade 1' if 141 – 150 Set to 'Grade 2' if 151 – 155 Set to 'Grade 3' if >155 Grade 4 is based on medical input Otherwise, set to 'Grade 0'
ATOXGRH Computation
Assign AVAL toxicity grading as follows If AVAL is not missing: Set to 'Grade 1' if 38.0 – 38.4 Set to 'Grade 2' if >38.4 – 38.9 Set to 'Grade 3' if >38.9 – 40.0 Set to 'Grade 4' if >40.0 Otherwise, set to 'Grade 0'
ATOXGRL Computation
Assign AVAL toxicity grading as follows If AVAL is not missing: Set to 'Grade 1' if 50 – 54 Set to 'Grade 2' if 45 – 49 Set to 'Grade 3' if <45 Grade 4 is based on medical input Otherwise, set to 'Grade 0'
ATOXGRL Computation
Assign AVAL toxicity grading as follows If AVAL is not missing: Set to 'Grade 1' if 85 – 89 Set to 'Grade 2' if 80 – 84 Set to 'Grade 3' if <80 Grade 4 is based on medical input Otherwise, set to Grade '0'
ATPT Computation
Set to ‘Day x’ if AVISIT='Illness Visit Day x' or 'Illness Visit y Day x' (see derivation of AVISIT)
AVAL Computation
Set to VS.VSSTRESN
AVISIT Computation
See ADVS.AVISIT from Additional ADaM Variable Definition Doc.

Additional ADaM Variable Definition

AWRANGE Computation
Set to '<=1 Pre-dose' for 'Baseline' 'Day 1 Post-dose' for 'Day 1' 'Day 2 - Day 43' for 'Day 29' 'Day 44 - Day 133' for 'Day 57' 'Day 134 – Day 301' for 'Day 209' 'Day 302 – Day 576' for 'Day 394' 'Day 577 - Day 773' for 'Day 759' 'Participant Decision Visit / OL-D1' for 'Participant Decision Visit / OL-D1' 'Day 2 – Day 43 Relative to Participant Decision Visit / OL-D1' for 'Open Label Day 29' 'Day 44 – Day 71 Relative to Participant Decision Visit / OL-D1' for 'Open Label Day 57' 'Illness Visit Day 1' for 'Illness Visit” and ATPT='Day 1' 'Illness Visit y Day 1' for 'Illness Visit y' and ATPT='Day 1' 'Illness Visit Day 2 - Illness Visit Day 35' for 'Illness Visit' and ATPT='Day 28' 'Illness Visit y Day 2 - Illness Visit y Day 35' for 'Illness Visit y' and ATPT='Day 28'
AWTARGET Computation
Set to 1 if AVISIT = 'Baseline' Set to 1 if AVISIT = 'Day 1' Set to 29 if AVISIT = 'Day 29' Set to 57 if AVISIT = 'Day 57' Set to 209 if AVISIT = 'Day 209' Set to 394 if AVISIT = 'Day 394' Set to 759 if AVISIT = 'Day 759' Set to ADY where AVISIT='Participant Decision Visit / OL-D1' for 'Participant Decision Visit / OL-D1' Set to ADY + 28 where AVISIT='Participant Decision Visit / OL-D1' for 'Open Label Day 29' Set to ADY + 56 where AVISIT='Participant Decision Visit / OL-D1' for 'Open Label Day 57' Set to ADY where AVISIT='Illness Visit' for 'Illness Visit' and ATPT='Day 1' Set to ADY where AVISIT='Illness Visit y' for 'Illness Visit y' and ATPT='Day 1' Set to ADY + 27 where AVISIT='Illness Visit' for 'Illness Visit' and ATPT='Day 28' Set to ADY + 27 where AVISIT='Illness Visit y' for 'Illness Visit y' and ATPT='Day 28'
AWTDIFF Computation
Set to absolute value of ( ADY - AWTARGET )
BASE Computation
Merge value of nonmissing AVAL where ABLFL = 'Y' by USUBJID and PARAMCD, then Set to AVAL where ABLFL = 'Y'
BTOXGRH Computation
Merge value of nonmissing ATOXGRH where ABLFL = 'Y' by USUBJID and PARAMCD
BTOXGRL Computation
Merge value of nonmissing ATOXGRL where ABLFL = 'Y' by USUBJID and PARAMCD
CHG Computation
For post baseline records only, if AVAL and BASE are both non-missing, set to AVAL - BASE Note: post-baseline records are defined as any result where ADTM > TR01SDTM or (ADTM=TR01SDTM and VSTPT^='PRE-DOSE') if time is available, if time is not available use (ADY=1 and VSTPT^='PRE-DOSE') or ADY > 1)
MDOSREF Computation
Set to 'Vaccination 1' if ( . < ADSL.TR01SDTM <= ADTM < ADSL.DOS2DTM ) or ( .< ADSL.TR01SDTM <= ADTM and ADSL.DOS2DTM is missing and (TR02SDTM is missing or .<ASTDTM<ADSL.TR02SDTM)), Set to 'Vaccination 2' if ( .< ADSL.DOS2DTM <= ADTM < ADSL.TR02SDTM ) or ( .< ADSL.DOS2DTM <= ADTM and ADSL.TR02SDTM is missing), Set to 'OL Vaccination 1' if (.<ADSL.TR02SDTM<=ADTM<ADSL.OLDO2DTM) or (.<ADSL.TR02SDTM<=ADTM and ADSL.OLDO2DTM is missing), Set to 'OL Vaccination 2' if .<ADSL.OLDO2DTM<=ADTM Note: using date variables for comparison when time part is not available
MRDDY Computation
Set to ADT – ADSL.TR01SDT+ 1 If MDOSREF='Vaccination 1', Set to ADT – ADSL.DOSE2DT+ 1 If MDOSREF='Vaccination 2', Set to ADT – ADSL.TR02SDT+ 1 If MDOSREF='OL Vaccination 1', Set to ADT – ADSL.OLDO2SDT+ 1 If MDOSREF='OL Vaccination 2'
PARAM Computation
VS.VSTEST ' (' ||VSSTRESU|| ')' if VSSTRESU is non-missing, if VSSTRESU is missing, use the non-missing VSSTRESU from the same VSTEST
PCHG Computation
Set to (CHG/BASE)*100 if BASE ne 0
SHIFT1 Computation
Only populate for post-baseline records where PARAMCD in ('PULSE', 'SYSBP') Set to BTOXGRL || ' to ' ||ATOXGRL if both of BTOXGRL and ATOXGRL are not missing If either BTOXGRL or ATOXGRL is missing: Set the missing BTOXGRL or ATOXGRL to 'UNK', then Set to BTOXGRL || ' to ' || ATOXGRL
SHIFT2 Computation
Only populate for post-baseline records Set to BTOXGRH || ' to '|| ATOXGRH if both of BTOXGRH and ATOXGRH are not missing If either BTOXGRH or ATOXGRH is missing: Set the missing BTOXGRH and ATOXGRH to 'UNK' Set to BTOXGRH || ' to ' || ATOXGRH
VSLOCSP Computation
Set to SUPPCM.QVAL where QNAM='VSLOCSP'
